```
T(n) = a*T(n/b) + f(n)
```

- Merge sort''s T(n) = 2T(n/2) + O(n) solves to **O(n log n)**.

## Linear-Time Sorts
- **Counting, radix and bucket** sorts beat the n log n bound by avoiding comparisons, given bounded keys.

### Tip
- Quick sort''s worst case O(n²) arises on already-sorted input with a poor pivot choice.', 2, 0),
  ('gate-core-cs-greedy-dynamic-programming-m01', 'gate-core-cs-greedy-dynamic-programming', 'Greedy & Dynamic Programming', '**Greedy** and **dynamic programming (DP)** are the two optimization paradigms most tested in GATE algorithm questions.

## Greedy Method
- Builds a solution by making the **locally optimal** choice at each step.
- Works only when the problem has the **greedy-choice property** and optimal substructure.

