2. The Saubhagya scheme aims at universal household electrification.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'Jan Dhan accounts come with RuPay cards, while Saubhagya targets electricity for all households.', 5),
  ('upsc-current-affairs-government-schemes-q07', 'upsc-current-affairs-government-schemes', 'The Production-Linked Incentive (PLI) scheme is designed primarily to boost:', 'Agricultural exports', 'Tourism', 'Rural employment', 'Domestic manufacturing', 'D', 'PLI offers incentives on incremental sales to expand domestic manufacturing under Make in India.', 6),
  ('upsc-current-affairs-government-schemes-q08', 'upsc-current-affairs-government-schemes', 'The Swachh Bharat Mission is chiefly aimed at achieving:', 'An open-defecation-free India', 'Free education', 'Universal banking', 'Affordable housing', 'A', 'The mission focuses on sanitation and making India open-defecation-free through toilet construction.', 7),
  ('upsc-polity-dpsp-and-fundamental-duties-q01', 'upsc-polity-dpsp-and-fundamental-duties', 'In which Part of the Constitution are the Directive Principles of State Policy contained?', 'Part IV (Articles 36-51)', 'Part III (Articles 12-35)', 'Part IVA (Article 51A)', 'Part II (Articles 5-11)', 'A', 'DPSP are contained in Part IV, Articles 36-51, and are borrowed from the Irish Constitution.', 0),
  ('upsc-polity-dpsp-and-fundamental-duties-q02', 'upsc-polity-dpsp-and-fundamental-duties', 'Fundamental Duties were added to the Constitution by which amendment?', '86th Amendment, 2002', '42nd Amendment, 1976', '44th Amendment, 1978', '73rd Amendment, 1992', 'B', 'The 42nd Amendment (1976) added Fundamental Duties on the recommendation of the Swaran Singh Committee.', 1),
  ('upsc-polity-dpsp-and-fundamental-duties-q03', 'upsc-polity-dpsp-and-fundamental-duties', 'Consider the following statements about DPSP:
1. They are justiciable and enforceable in courts.
2. They were borrowed from the Irish Constitution.
Which is/are correct?', '2 only', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'A', 'DPSP are non-justiciable but fundamental in governance; they were borrowed from the Irish Constitution.', 2),
  ('upsc-polity-dpsp-and-fundamental-duties-q04', 'upsc-polity-dpsp-and-fundamental-duties', 'Which Article of the Constitution provides for a Uniform Civil Code?', 'Article 40', 'Article 44', 'Article 39A', 'Article 50', 'B', 'Article 44 directs the State to secure a Uniform Civil Code; it is a liberal-intellectual directive.', 3),
  ('upsc-polity-dpsp-and-fundamental-duties-q05', 'upsc-polity-dpsp-and-fundamental-duties', 'The Eleventh Fundamental Duty, added by the 86th Amendment (2002), relates to:', 'Protecting the environment', 'A parent''s duty to provide education to a child aged 6-14', 'Safeguarding public property', 'Promoting scientific temper', 'B', 'The 86th Amendment added the duty of a parent to provide education opportunities to a child aged 6-14.', 4),
  ('upsc-polity-dpsp-and-fundamental-duties-q06', 'upsc-polity-dpsp-and-fundamental-duties', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Article 50 calls for separation of the judiciary from the executive.
2. Fundamental Duties are enshrined in Part IVA under Article 51A.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', '2 only', 'B', 'Article 50 mandates judiciary-executive separation; Fundamental Duties sit in Part IVA, Article 51A.', 5),
  ('upsc-polity-dpsp-and-fundamental-duties-q07', 'upsc-polity-dpsp-and-fundamental-duties', 'Which case held that balance between Fundamental Rights and DPSP is part of the basic structure?', 'Minerva Mills case (1980)', 'Maneka Gandhi case (1978)', 'Golaknath case (1967)', 'Gopalan case (1950)', 'A', 'In Minerva Mills (1980), the Supreme Court held the balance between FRs and DPSP is part of the basic structure.', 6),
  ('upsc-polity-dpsp-and-fundamental-duties-q08', 'upsc-polity-dpsp-and-fundamental-duties', 'Article 39A, providing for free legal aid and equal justice, was added by which amendment?', '42nd Amendment', '44th Amendment', '86th Amendment', '1st Amendment', 'A', 'Article 39A on equal justice and free legal aid was inserted by the 42nd Amendment of 1976.', 7),
  ('upsc-polity-judiciary-and-judicial-review-q01', 'upsc-polity-judiciary-and-judicial-review', 'Under which Article is the Supreme Court of India established?', 'Article 124', 'Article 32', 'Article 137', 'Article 143', 'A', 'Article 124 establishes the Supreme Court of India and provides for its composition.', 0),
  ('upsc-polity-judiciary-and-judicial-review-q02', 'upsc-polity-judiciary-and-judicial-review', 'What is the present sanctioned strength of judges in the Supreme Court (including the CJI)?', '34', '26', '30', '31', 'A', 'The sanctioned strength is 34: the Chief Justice of India plus up to 33 other judges.', 1),
  ('upsc-polity-judiciary-and-judicial-review-q03', 'upsc-polity-judiciary-and-judicial-review', 'Consider the following statements:
1. A Supreme Court judge holds office until 65 years of age.
2. Article 137 empowers the court to review its own judgments.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', '1 only', 'A', 'SC judges retire at 65; Article 137 grants the power to review the court''s own judgments.', 2),
  ('upsc-polity-judiciary-and-judicial-review-q04', 'upsc-polity-judiciary-and-judicial-review', 'The advisory jurisdiction of the Supreme Court is provided under which Article?', 'Article 131', 'Article 143', 'Article 136', 'Article 132', 'B', 'Article 143 allows the President to seek the advisory opinion of the Supreme Court.', 3),
  ('upsc-polity-judiciary-and-judicial-review-q05', 'upsc-polity-judiciary-and-judicial-review', 'The 99th Amendment that created the NJAC was struck down by the Supreme Court in which year?', '2010', '2013', '2018', '2015', 'D', 'The Supreme Court struck down the NJAC (99th Amendment) in 2015, restoring the collegium system.', 4),
  ('upsc-polity-judiciary-and-judicial-review-q06', 'upsc-polity-judiciary-and-judicial-review', 'Consider the following statements about writ jurisdiction:
1. A High Court issues writs under Article 226.
2. Article 226 is wider than Article 32 as it covers legal rights too.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'B', 'High Courts issue writs under Article 226, which is wider than Article 32 since it covers legal rights too.', 5),
  ('upsc-polity-judiciary-and-judicial-review-q07', 'upsc-polity-judiciary-and-judicial-review', 'Public Interest Litigation (PIL) in India was pioneered chiefly by which judges?', 'H.J. Kania and M. Patanjali Sastri', 'M. Hidayatullah and S.M. Sikri', 'P.N. Bhagwati and V.R. Krishna Iyer', 'A.N. Ray and Y.V. Chandrachud', 'C', 'Justices P.N. Bhagwati and V.R. Krishna Iyer pioneered PIL by relaxing the rule of locus standi.', 6),
  ('upsc-polity-judiciary-and-judicial-review-q08', 'upsc-polity-judiciary-and-judicial-review', 'The collegium system for the appointment of judges evolved from which cases?', 'The Second and Third Judges Cases', 'The First and Second Judges Cases', 'The Kesavananda and Minerva cases', 'The Golaknath and Maneka Gandhi cases', 'A', 'The collegium system evolved primarily from the Second (1993) and Third (1998) Judges Cases.', 7),
  ('upsc-polity-constitutional-and-statutory-bodies-q01', 'upsc-polity-constitutional-and-statutory-bodies', 'Which one of the following is a constitutional body?', 'Election Commission of India', 'National Human Rights Commission', 'NITI Aayog', 'Central Information Commission', 'A', 'The Election Commission is a constitutional body under Article 324; the others are non-constitutional or statutory.', 0),
  ('upsc-polity-constitutional-and-statutory-bodies-q02', 'upsc-polity-constitutional-and-statutory-bodies', 'The Comptroller and Auditor General of India is provided for under which Article?', 'Article 280', 'Article 324', 'Article 315', 'Article 148', 'D', 'Article 148 provides for the CAG, the guardian of the public purse who audits government accounts.', 1),
  ('upsc-polity-constitutional-and-statutory-bodies-q03', 'upsc-polity-constitutional-and-statutory-bodies', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Finance Commission is constituted under Article 280.
2. It is set up every five years to recommend tax devolution.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'Both 1 and 2', 'D', 'The Finance Commission, under Article 280, is constituted every five years for Centre-State tax devolution.', 2),
  ('upsc-polity-constitutional-and-statutory-bodies-q04', 'upsc-polity-constitutional-and-statutory-bodies', 'The National Human Rights Commission (NHRC) was established under which law?', 'Protection of Human Rights Act, 1993', 'Lokpal and Lokayuktas Act, 2013', 'RTI Act, 2005', 'Right to Education Act, 2009', 'A', 'The NHRC is a statutory body set up under the Protection of Human Rights Act, 1993.', 3),
  ('upsc-polity-constitutional-and-statutory-bodies-q05', 'upsc-polity-constitutional-and-statutory-bodies', 'The National Commission for Backward Classes became a constitutional body under which Article?', 'Article 280', 'Article 338', 'Article 324', 'Article 338B', 'D', 'The NCBC gained constitutional status under Article 338B via the 102nd Amendment (2018).', 4),
  ('upsc-polity-constitutional-and-statutory-bodies-q06', 'upsc-polity-constitutional-and-statutory-bodies', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The UPSC is a constitutional body under Article 315.
2. The Lokpal is a statutory body created in 2013.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', '2 only', '1 only', 'A', 'The UPSC is constitutional under Article 315; the Lokpal is statutory under the 2013 Act.', 5),
  ('upsc-polity-constitutional-and-statutory-bodies-q07', 'upsc-polity-constitutional-and-statutory-bodies', 'The Central Information Commission functions under which Act?', 'Protection of Human Rights Act, 1993', 'Right to Information Act, 2005', 'Companies Act, 2013', 'Lokpal and Lokayuktas Act, 2013', 'B', 'The CIC is a statutory body that functions under the Right to Information Act, 2005.', 6),
  ('upsc-polity-constitutional-and-statutory-bodies-q08', 'upsc-polity-constitutional-and-statutory-bodies', 'The Attorney General of India is provided for under which Article?', 'Article 315', 'Article 148', 'Article 280', 'Article 76', 'D', 'Article 76 provides for the Attorney General, the highest law officer of the Union.', 7),
  ('upsc-modern-history-moderates-and-extremists-q01', 'upsc-modern-history-moderates-and-extremists', 'Who was the first president of the Indian National Congress?', 'W.C. Bonnerjee', 'Dadabhai Naoroji', 'A.O. Hume', 'Surendranath Banerjee', 'A', 'W.C. Bonnerjee presided over the first Congress session in 1885; A.O. Hume founded the party.', 0),
  ('upsc-modern-history-moderates-and-extremists-q02', 'upsc-modern-history-moderates-and-extremists', 'The ''Drain Theory'' explaining the economic exploitation of India was propounded by:', 'Gopal Krishna Gokhale', 'Dadabhai Naoroji', 'Bal Gangadhar Tilak', 'Bipin Chandra Pal', 'B', 'Dadabhai Naoroji propounded the Drain Theory in his work Poverty and Un-British Rule in India.', 1),
  ('upsc-modern-history-moderates-and-extremists-q03', 'upsc-modern-history-moderates-and-extremists', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Congress split into Moderates and Extremists at the Surat session of 1907.
2. They reunited at the Lucknow session of 1916.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'B', 'The Surat Split occurred in 1907 and the two factions reunited at Lucknow in 1916.', 2),
  ('upsc-modern-history-moderates-and-extremists-q04', 'upsc-modern-history-moderates-and-extremists', 'Which trio is collectively known as ''Lal-Bal-Pal''?', 'Lala Hardayal, Tilak, B.G. Pal', 'Lajpat Rai, Bonnerjee, Pherozeshah Mehta', 'Lajpat Rai, Tilak, Bipin Chandra Pal', 'Lajpat Rai, Gokhale, Naoroji', 'C', 'Lal-Bal-Pal were the extremist leaders Lala Lajpat Rai, Bal Gangadhar Tilak and Bipin Chandra Pal.', 3),
  ('upsc-modern-history-moderates-and-extremists-q05', 'upsc-modern-history-moderates-and-extremists', 'The slogan ''Swaraj is my birthright and I shall have it'' was given by:', 'Lala Lajpat Rai', 'Bipin Chandra Pal', 'Bal Gangadhar Tilak', 'Aurobindo Ghosh', 'C', 'Bal Gangadhar Tilak gave the famous slogan asserting Swaraj as a birthright.', 4),
  ('upsc-modern-history-moderates-and-extremists-q06', 'upsc-modern-history-moderates-and-extremists', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Moderates relied on petitions, prayers and protests.
2. The Swadeshi Movement was triggered by the Partition of Bengal in 1905.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'D', 'Moderates used the 3 Ps; the 1905 Partition of Bengal triggered the Swadeshi Movement.', 5),
  ('upsc-modern-history-moderates-and-extremists-q07', 'upsc-modern-history-moderates-and-extremists', 'The Indian National Congress was founded in which year?', '1857', '1905', '1885', '1916', 'C', 'The Indian National Congress was founded in 1885 by A.O. Hume.', 6),
  ('upsc-modern-history-moderates-and-extremists-q08', 'upsc-modern-history-moderates-and-extremists', 'The Lucknow session of 1916 is notable because:', 'It marked the founding of the Congress', 'It launched the Quit India Movement', 'It saw the Lucknow Pact with the Muslim League', 'It abolished the Drain Theory', 'C', 'The 1916 Lucknow session reunited Congress factions and produced the Lucknow Pact with the Muslim League.', 7),
  ('upsc-modern-history-gandhian-mass-movements-q01', 'upsc-modern-history-gandhian-mass-movements', 'Gandhi''s first Satyagraha in India, in 1917, was launched at:', 'Kheda', 'Ahmedabad', 'Champaran', 'Dandi', 'C', 'The Champaran Satyagraha of 1917 opposed the tinkathia system imposed on indigo cultivators in Bihar.', 0),
  ('upsc-modern-history-gandhian-mass-movements-q02', 'upsc-modern-history-gandhian-mass-movements', 'The Non-Cooperation Movement was withdrawn following which incident?', 'Jallianwala Bagh massacre', 'Chauri Chaura incident', 'Failure of the Cripps Mission', 'Partition of Bengal', 'B', 'Gandhi withdrew the Non-Cooperation Movement in 1922 after the violent Chauri Chaura incident.', 1),
  ('upsc-modern-history-gandhian-mass-movements-q03', 'upsc-modern-history-gandhian-mass-movements', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Dandi March began on 12 March 1930.
2. The Civil Disobedience Movement broke the salt law.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', '1 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'A', 'The Dandi March started on 12 March 1930 and launched Civil Disobedience by breaking the salt law.', 2),
  ('upsc-modern-history-gandhian-mass-movements-q04', 'upsc-modern-history-gandhian-mass-movements', 'The slogan ''Do or Die'' is associated with which movement?', 'Non-Cooperation Movement', 'Quit India Movement', 'Swadeshi Movement', 'Civil Disobedience Movement', 'B', 'Gandhi gave the ''Do or Die'' call during the Quit India Movement of 1942.', 3),
  ('upsc-modern-history-gandhian-mass-movements-q05', 'upsc-modern-history-gandhian-mass-movements', 'The Kheda Satyagraha of 1918 was launched for:', 'Remission of land revenue during crop failure', 'Abolition of the tinkathia system', 'Higher wages for mill workers', 'Repeal of the salt tax', 'A', 'The Kheda Satyagraha in Gujarat demanded remission of land revenue after crop failure.', 4),
  ('upsc-modern-history-gandhian-mass-movements-q06', 'upsc-modern-history-gandhian-mass-movements', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Quit India Movement was triggered by the failure of the Cripps Mission.
2. The Gandhi-Irwin Pact led to Congress joining the Second Round Table Conference.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'Both 1 and 2', 'D', 'Quit India followed the Cripps Mission failure; the 1931 Gandhi-Irwin Pact preceded the Second Round Table Conference.', 5),
  ('upsc-modern-history-gandhian-mass-movements-q07', 'upsc-modern-history-gandhian-mass-movements', 'In which year did Mahatma Gandhi return to India from South Africa?', '1915', '1909', '1920', '1919', 'A', 'Gandhi returned to India in 1915 and transformed the freedom struggle into a mass movement.', 6),
  ('upsc-modern-history-gandhian-mass-movements-q08', 'upsc-modern-history-gandhian-mass-movements', 'Gandhi''s first hunger strike in India was undertaken during which event?', 'Champaran Satyagraha', 'Kheda Satyagraha', 'Ahmedabad Mill Strike', 'Dandi March', 'C', 'Gandhi undertook his first hunger strike during the 1918 Ahmedabad Mill Strike.', 7),
  ('upsc-modern-history-socio-religious-reform-movements-q01', 'upsc-modern-history-socio-religious-reform-movements', 'The Brahmo Samaj was founded in 1828 by:', 'Ishwar Chandra Vidyasagar', 'Dayananda Saraswati', 'Swami Vivekananda', 'Raja Ram Mohan Roy', 'D', 'Raja Ram Mohan Roy founded the Brahmo Samaj in 1828 and is called the Father of Indian Renaissance.', 0),
  ('upsc-modern-history-socio-religious-reform-movements-q02', 'upsc-modern-history-socio-religious-reform-movements', 'The slogan ''Back to the Vedas'' was given by:', 'Raja Ram Mohan Roy', 'Jyotiba Phule', 'Dayananda Saraswati', 'Sir Syed Ahmed Khan', 'C', 'Dayananda Saraswati, founder of the Arya Samaj (1875), gave the slogan ''Back to the Vedas''.', 1),
  ('upsc-modern-history-socio-religious-reform-movements-q03', 'upsc-modern-history-socio-religious-reform-movements', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Sati was abolished by Lord William Bentinck in 1829.
2. Raja Ram Mohan Roy campaigned against Sati.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'B', 'Lord William Bentinck abolished Sati in 1829, supported by Raja Ram Mohan Roy''s campaign.', 2),
  ('upsc-modern-history-socio-religious-reform-movements-q04', 'upsc-modern-history-socio-religious-reform-movements', 'The Satyashodhak Samaj (1873) was founded by:', 'Swami Vivekananda', 'Colonel Olcott', 'Dayananda Saraswati', 'Jyotiba Phule', 'D', 'Jyotiba Phule founded the Satyashodhak Samaj in 1873 to fight caste oppression.', 3),
  ('upsc-modern-history-socio-religious-reform-movements-q05', 'upsc-modern-history-socio-religious-reform-movements', 'Who championed the cause of widow remarriage, leading to the Act of 1856?', 'Sir Syed Ahmed Khan', 'Ishwar Chandra Vidyasagar', 'Swami Vivekananda', 'Madame Blavatsky', 'B', 'Ishwar Chandra Vidyasagar championed widow remarriage, which led to the Widow Remarriage Act of 1856.', 4),
  ('upsc-modern-history-socio-religious-reform-movements-q06', 'upsc-modern-history-socio-religious-reform-movements', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Ramakrishna Mission was founded by Swami Vivekananda in 1897.
2. The Aligarh Movement was led by Sir Syed Ahmed Khan.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'Both 1 and 2', 'D', 'Vivekananda founded the Ramakrishna Mission in 1897; Sir Syed Ahmed Khan led the Aligarh Movement.', 5),
  ('upsc-modern-history-socio-religious-reform-movements-q07', 'upsc-modern-history-socio-religious-reform-movements', 'The Shuddhi movement, aimed at reconversion, was started by which organisation?', 'Theosophical Society', 'Brahmo Samaj', 'Ramakrishna Mission', 'Arya Samaj', 'D', 'The Arya Samaj, founded by Dayananda Saraswati, started the Shuddhi reconversion movement.', 6),
  ('upsc-modern-history-socio-religious-reform-movements-q08', 'upsc-modern-history-socio-religious-reform-movements', 'The Theosophical Society was founded in 1875 by:', 'Annie Besant alone', 'Sir Syed Ahmed Khan', 'Madame Blavatsky and Colonel Olcott', 'Raja Ram Mohan Roy', 'C', 'The Theosophical Society was founded in 1875 by Madame Blavatsky and Colonel Olcott.', 7),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-indus-valley-civilisation-q01', 'upsc-ancient-history-indus-valley-civilisation', 'Mohenjo-daro is situated on the banks of which river?', 'Indus', 'Ravi', 'Ghaggar', 'Sutlej', 'A', 'Mohenjo-daro, meaning Mound of the Dead, is located on the Indus river and housed the Great Bath.', 0),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-indus-valley-civilisation-q02', 'upsc-ancient-history-indus-valley-civilisation', 'The site of Lothal is best known for its:', 'Artificial dockyard', 'Citadel', 'Great Bath', 'Pillared hall', 'A', 'Lothal in Gujarat had an artificial dockyard, evidence of Harappan maritime trade.', 1),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-indus-valley-civilisation-q03', 'upsc-ancient-history-indus-valley-civilisation', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Harappa was discovered in 1921 by Daya Ram Sahni.
2. Mohenjo-daro was discovered in 1922 by R.D. Banerji.
Which is/are correct?', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', '1 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'B', 'Harappa was found in 1921 by Daya Ram Sahni and Mohenjo-daro in 1922 by R.D. Banerji.', 2),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-indus-valley-civilisation-q04', 'upsc-ancient-history-indus-valley-civilisation', 'The Harappans traded with Mesopotamia, where their land was referred to as:', 'Meluhha', 'Magan', 'Dilmun', 'Punt', 'A', 'Mesopotamian records refer to the Indus region as Meluhha.', 3),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-indus-valley-civilisation-q05', 'upsc-ancient-history-indus-valley-civilisation', 'The Indus Valley Civilisation belonged to which technological age?', 'Iron Age', 'Bronze Age', 'Stone Age', 'Copper Age only', 'B', 'The IVC was a Bronze Age civilisation flourishing roughly 2600-1900 BCE.', 4),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-indus-valley-civilisation-q06', 'upsc-ancient-history-indus-valley-civilisation', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Harappan script is pictographic and remains undeciphered.
2. The Pashupati seal is regarded as a proto-Shiva representation.
Which is/are correct?', '2 only', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'The pictographic Harappan script is undeciphered, and the Pashupati seal is seen as proto-Shiva.', 5),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-indus-valley-civilisation-q07', 'upsc-ancient-history-indus-valley-civilisation', 'Harappan towns were typically laid out on which pattern?', 'Grid pattern', 'Radial pattern', 'Concentric circles', 'Random clusters', 'A', 'Harappan towns followed a grid pattern with a citadel and a lower town, plus advanced drainage.', 6),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-indus-valley-civilisation-q08', 'upsc-ancient-history-indus-valley-civilisation', 'Which deity was widely worshipped in the Indus Valley Civilisation?', 'The Mother Goddess', 'Indra', 'Vishnu', 'Surya', 'A', 'The Harappans worshipped the Mother Goddess and a proto-Shiva Pashupati figure.', 7),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-mauryan-empire-q01', 'upsc-ancient-history-mauryan-empire', 'Who was the founder of the Mauryan Empire?', 'Chandragupta Maurya', 'Bindusara', 'Ashoka', 'Pushyamitra Shunga', 'A', 'Chandragupta Maurya founded the empire in 322 BCE with the guidance of Chanakya (Kautilya).', 0),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-mauryan-empire-q02', 'upsc-ancient-history-mauryan-empire', 'The Greek envoy who wrote ''Indica'' at the Mauryan court was:', 'Seleucus', 'Fa-Hien', 'Megasthenes', 'Hiuen Tsang', 'C', 'Megasthenes, the Greek envoy of Seleucus, wrote Indica at Chandragupta Maurya''s court.', 1),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-mauryan-empire-q03', 'upsc-ancient-history-mauryan-empire', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Kalinga War was fought in 261 BCE.
2. After the war Ashoka propagated his policy of Dhamma.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'The Kalinga War of 261 BCE transformed Ashoka, who then propagated Dhamma.', 2),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-mauryan-empire-q04', 'upsc-ancient-history-mauryan-empire', 'The Arthashastra, a treatise on statecraft, was authored by:', 'Megasthenes', 'Kautilya (Chanakya)', 'Harisena', 'Varahamihira', 'B', 'Kautilya, also known as Chanakya, authored the Arthashastra on statecraft, economy and espionage.', 3),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-mauryan-empire-q05', 'upsc-ancient-history-mauryan-empire', 'The Lion Capital of Sarnath, India''s national emblem, was erected by:', 'Chandragupta Maurya', 'Bindusara', 'Ashoka', 'Samudragupta', 'C', 'Ashoka''s Lion Capital of Sarnath was adopted as India''s national emblem.', 4),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-mauryan-empire-q06', 'upsc-ancient-history-mauryan-empire', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Ashoka''s edicts were inscribed in scripts including Brahmi and Kharosthi.
2. The Mauryan dynasty ended with the assassination of Brihadratha by Pushyamitra Shunga.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', '1 only', 'A', 'Ashoka''s edicts used Brahmi, Kharosthi, Greek and Aramaic; Pushyamitra Shunga killed Brihadratha in 185 BCE.', 5),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-mauryan-empire-q07', 'upsc-ancient-history-mauryan-empire', 'Which Mauryan ruler was known by the title ''Amitraghata''?', 'Bindusara', 'Chandragupta Maurya', 'Ashoka', 'Dasharatha', 'A', 'Bindusara, son of Chandragupta, was known as Amitraghata, the slayer of foes.', 6),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-mauryan-empire-q08', 'upsc-ancient-history-mauryan-empire', 'Mauryan provinces were administered by princes who held which title?', 'Mahamatras', 'Kumaras', 'Amatyas', 'Rajukas', 'B', 'Mauryan provinces were governed by princes known as Kumaras.', 7),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-gupta-age-q01', 'upsc-ancient-history-gupta-age', 'Which Gupta ruler is described as the ''Napoleon of India'' by historian V.A. Smith?', 'Chandragupta I', 'Samudragupta', 'Chandragupta II', 'Skandagupta', 'B', 'Samudragupta''s extensive conquests earned him the title ''Napoleon of India'' from V.A. Smith.', 0),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-gupta-age-q02', 'upsc-ancient-history-gupta-age', 'The Allahabad Pillar inscription (Prayag Prashasti) was composed by:', 'Kalidasa', 'Harisena', 'Aryabhata', 'Varahamihira', 'B', 'Harisena composed the Allahabad Pillar inscription recording Samudragupta''s conquests.', 1),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-gupta-age-q03', 'upsc-ancient-history-gupta-age', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Aryabhata wrote the Aryabhatiya and proposed Earth''s rotation.
2. Fa-Hien visited India during Chandragupta II''s reign.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'Aryabhata wrote the Aryabhatiya; the Chinese pilgrim Fa-Hien visited during Chandragupta II''s reign.', 2),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-gupta-age-q04', 'upsc-ancient-history-gupta-age', 'Chandragupta II earned fame by defeating which foreign rulers?', 'The Hunas', 'The Shakas', 'The Kushanas', 'The Greeks', 'B', 'Chandragupta II Vikramaditya defeated the Shakas, extending Gupta power to western India.', 3),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-gupta-age-q05', 'upsc-ancient-history-gupta-age', 'Kalidasa, the celebrated Gupta-era poet, authored which work?', 'Aryabhatiya', 'Abhijnanashakuntalam', 'Brihat Samhita', 'Indica', 'B', 'Kalidasa wrote Abhijnanashakuntalam; the Brihat Samhita was by Varahamihira.', 4),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-gupta-age-q06', 'upsc-ancient-history-gupta-age', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Gupta age is called the Golden Age of India.
2. The decline of the Guptas was hastened by Huna invasions under Toramana and Mihirakula.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'Both 1 and 2', 'D', 'The Gupta age is the Golden Age; Huna invasions led by Toramana and Mihirakula hastened its decline.', 5),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-gupta-age-q07', 'upsc-ancient-history-gupta-age', 'Who founded the Gupta dynasty and married Kumaradevi of the Licchavis?', 'Samudragupta', 'Sri Gupta', 'Chandragupta II', 'Chandragupta I', 'D', 'Chandragupta I founded the imperial Gupta line and strengthened it by marrying Licchavi princess Kumaradevi.', 6),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-gupta-age-q08', 'upsc-ancient-history-gupta-age', 'The Mehrauli Iron Pillar is a notable example of Gupta-era advances in:', 'Metallurgy', 'Painting', 'Astronomy', 'Town planning', 'A', 'The rust-resistant Mehrauli Iron Pillar demonstrates the high metallurgical skill of the Gupta period.', 7),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-buddhism-and-jainism-q01', 'upsc-ancient-history-buddhism-and-jainism', 'Gautama Buddha attained enlightenment at which place?', 'Lumbini', 'Bodh Gaya', 'Kushinagar', 'Sarnath', 'B', 'Buddha attained enlightenment at Bodh Gaya; he was born at Lumbini and gave his first sermon at Sarnath.', 0),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-buddhism-and-jainism-q02', 'upsc-ancient-history-buddhism-and-jainism', 'Who was the 24th and last Tirthankara of Jainism?', 'Rishabhanatha', 'Parshvanatha', 'Neminatha', 'Mahavira', 'D', 'Mahavira was the 24th Tirthankara; Rishabhanatha was the first and Parshvanatha the 23rd.', 1),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-buddhism-and-jainism-q03', 'upsc-ancient-history-buddhism-and-jainism', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Buddha''s first sermon at Sarnath is called Dharmachakra Pravartana.
2. Buddhism follows the Middle Path.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'The first sermon at Sarnath is the Dharmachakra Pravartana; Buddhism advocates the Middle Path.', 2),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-buddhism-and-jainism-q04', 'upsc-ancient-history-buddhism-and-jainism', 'The Fourth Buddhist Council, which split Buddhism into Hinayana and Mahayana, was held under:', 'Kanishka', 'Bindusara', 'Ajatashatru', 'Ashoka', 'A', 'The Fourth Buddhist Council was held under Kanishka and led to the Hinayana-Mahayana split.', 3),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-buddhism-and-jainism-q05', 'upsc-ancient-history-buddhism-and-jainism', 'The Three Jewels (Triratna) of Jainism are right faith, right knowledge and:', 'Right conduct', 'Right livelihood', 'Right speech', 'Right mindfulness', 'A', 'The Jain Triratna comprises right faith, right knowledge and right conduct.', 4),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-buddhism-and-jainism-q06', 'upsc-ancient-history-buddhism-and-jainism', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Third Buddhist Council was held under Ashoka at Pataliputra.
2. Early Buddhist texts (Tripitaka) were written in Pali.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '1 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', '2 only', 'A', 'The Third Council met under Ashoka at Pataliputra; the Tripitaka was composed in Pali.', 5),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-buddhism-and-jainism-q07', 'upsc-ancient-history-buddhism-and-jainism', 'The two principal sects of Jainism are:', 'Hinayana and Mahayana', 'Saguna and Nirguna', 'Theravada and Vajrayana', 'Digambara and Svetambara', 'D', 'Jainism''s two principal sects are the Digambara (sky-clad) and Svetambara (white-clad).', 6),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-buddhism-and-jainism-q08', 'upsc-ancient-history-buddhism-and-jainism', 'The core ethical principle emphasised by Jainism is:', 'Ahimsa (non-violence)', 'Moksha through ritual', 'Animal sacrifice', 'Idol worship', 'A', 'Ahimsa, or non-violence, is the central ethical principle of Jainism.', 7),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-delhi-sultanate-q01', 'upsc-medieval-history-delhi-sultanate', 'Who founded the Slave (Mamluk) dynasty of the Delhi Sultanate in 1206?', 'Iltutmish', 'Qutb-ud-din Aibak', 'Balban', 'Jalal-ud-din Khalji', 'B', 'Qutb-ud-din Aibak founded the Slave dynasty in 1206 and began the Qutub Minar.', 0),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-delhi-sultanate-q02', 'upsc-medieval-history-delhi-sultanate', 'The only woman to rule the Delhi Sultanate was:', 'Chand Bibi', 'Razia Sultana', 'Nur Jahan', 'Rani Durgavati', 'B', 'Razia Sultana, daughter of Iltutmish, was the only woman to rule the Delhi Sultanate.', 1),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-delhi-sultanate-q03', 'upsc-medieval-history-delhi-sultanate', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Alauddin Khalji introduced market price control reforms.
2. He repelled repeated Mongol invasions.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'Both 1 and 2', 'D', 'Alauddin Khalji introduced market control reforms and successfully repelled Mongol invasions.', 2),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-delhi-sultanate-q04', 'upsc-medieval-history-delhi-sultanate', 'The transfer of capital to Daulatabad and the issue of token currency are associated with:', 'Firoz Shah Tughlaq', 'Muhammad bin Tughlaq', 'Ghiyasuddin Tughlaq', 'Bahlol Lodi', 'B', 'Muhammad bin Tughlaq shifted the capital to Daulatabad and introduced token currency.', 3),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-delhi-sultanate-q05', 'upsc-medieval-history-delhi-sultanate', 'Under the iqta system of the Delhi Sultanate, an iqta referred to:', 'A unit of currency', 'A military rank', 'An assignment of land revenue in lieu of salary', 'A religious tax', 'C', 'The iqta system assigned land revenue to officials in place of a cash salary.', 4),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-delhi-sultanate-q06', 'upsc-medieval-history-delhi-sultanate', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Qutub Minar was begun by Qutb-ud-din Aibak and completed by Iltutmish.
2. The Delhi Sultanate ended with the First Battle of Panipat in 1526.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', '1 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'A', 'Aibak began and Iltutmish completed the Qutub Minar; Babur ended the Sultanate at Panipat in 1526.', 5),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-delhi-sultanate-q07', 'upsc-medieval-history-delhi-sultanate', 'Which ruler founded the Lodi dynasty, the last of the Delhi Sultanate?', 'Khizr Khan', 'Ibrahim Lodi', 'Sikandar Lodi', 'Bahlol Lodi', 'D', 'Bahlol Lodi founded the Lodi dynasty in 1451; Ibrahim Lodi was the last Sultan.', 6),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-delhi-sultanate-q08', 'upsc-medieval-history-delhi-sultanate', 'Firoz Shah Tughlaq is particularly remembered for:', 'Introducing token currency', 'Levying jizya and building canals', 'Transferring the capital to Daulatabad', 'Defeating Babur at Panipat', 'B', 'Firoz Shah Tughlaq levied the jizya tax and built irrigation canals.', 7),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-mughal-empire-q01', 'upsc-medieval-history-mughal-empire', 'The Mughal Empire was founded after the First Battle of Panipat (1526) by:', 'Babur', 'Akbar', 'Sher Shah Suri', 'Humayun', 'A', 'Babur founded the Mughal Empire after defeating Ibrahim Lodi at the First Battle of Panipat in 1526.', 0),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-mughal-empire-q02', 'upsc-medieval-history-mughal-empire', 'Who introduced the silver coin ''rupiya'' and built the Grand Trunk Road?', 'Aurangzeb', 'Akbar', 'Babur', 'Sher Shah Suri', 'D', 'Sher Shah Suri introduced the rupiya and developed the Grand Trunk Road.', 1),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-mughal-empire-q03', 'upsc-medieval-history-mughal-empire', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Akbar abolished the jizya tax.
2. Akbar started the Din-i-Ilahi in 1582.
Which is/are correct?', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', '1 only', 'B', 'Akbar abolished the jizya and founded the syncretic Din-i-Ilahi in 1582.', 2),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-mughal-empire-q04', 'upsc-medieval-history-mughal-empire', 'The Zabti or Dahsala revenue system was developed under Akbar by:', 'Raja Todar Mal', 'Abul Fazl', 'Birbal', 'Man Singh', 'A', 'Raja Todar Mal developed the Zabti (Dahsala) land revenue system under Akbar.', 3),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-mughal-empire-q05', 'upsc-medieval-history-mughal-empire', 'In the Mansabdari system, the ranks ''zat'' and ''sawar'' indicated respectively:', 'Tax rate and revenue share', 'Personal status and cavalry obligation', 'Religious rank and military rank', 'Land grant and salary', 'B', 'Zat denoted personal status and pay, while sawar indicated the number of cavalry to be maintained.', 4),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-mughal-empire-q06', 'upsc-medieval-history-mughal-empire', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Shah Jahan built the Taj Mahal.
2. Mughal painting peaked under Jahangir.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'C', 'Shah Jahan built the Taj Mahal and Mughal painting reached its zenith under Jahangir.', 5),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-mughal-empire-q07', 'upsc-medieval-history-mughal-empire', 'Which Mughal emperor re-imposed the jizya and expanded the empire to its greatest extent?', 'Akbar', 'Jahangir', 'Shah Jahan', 'Aurangzeb', 'D', 'Aurangzeb re-imposed the jizya and took the empire to its greatest territorial extent.', 6),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-mughal-empire-q08', 'upsc-medieval-history-mughal-empire', 'Mughal emperor Humayun is best known for:', 'Building Fatehpur Sikri', 'Starting the Din-i-Ilahi', 'Building the Taj Mahal', 'Losing his throne to Sher Shah Suri', 'D', 'Humayun temporarily lost the throne to Sher Shah Suri before regaining it in 1555.', 7),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-bhakti-and-sufi-movements-q01', 'upsc-medieval-history-bhakti-and-sufi-movements', 'Which saint founded Sikhism?', 'Chaitanya', 'Ramananda', 'Kabir', 'Guru Nanak', 'D', 'Guru Nanak founded Sikhism; he was a Nirguna saint who rejected ritualism and caste.', 0),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-bhakti-and-sufi-movements-q02', 'upsc-medieval-history-bhakti-and-sufi-movements', 'The Bhakti saint Mirabai was devoted to:', 'Vishnu as Vithoba', 'Shiva', 'Rama', 'Krishna', 'D', 'Mirabai of Rajasthan was a devotee of Krishna and a celebrated Bhakti poet.', 1),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-bhakti-and-sufi-movements-q03', 'upsc-medieval-history-bhakti-and-sufi-movements', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Kabir and Guru Nanak were Nirguna saints.
2. Saguna saints worshipped a god with form.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'B', 'Kabir and Guru Nanak belonged to the Nirguna (formless) school; Saguna saints worshipped a god with form.', 2),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-bhakti-and-sufi-movements-q04', 'upsc-medieval-history-bhakti-and-sufi-movements', 'The Chishti Sufi order in India is most closely associated with which saint of Ajmer?', 'Nizamuddin Auliya', 'Khwaja Moinuddin Chishti', 'Baba Farid', 'Sheikh Bahauddin Zakariya', 'B', 'Khwaja Moinuddin Chishti of Ajmer founded the influential Chishti order in India.', 3),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-bhakti-and-sufi-movements-q05', 'upsc-medieval-history-bhakti-and-sufi-movements', 'In Sufi tradition, a ''khanqah'' refers to:', 'A mystical order', 'A devotional song', 'A Sufi hospice', 'A holy relic', 'C', 'A khanqah was a Sufi hospice where the saint lived and disciples gathered.', 4),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-bhakti-and-sufi-movements-q06', 'upsc-medieval-history-bhakti-and-sufi-movements', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Sufi orders were organised into silsilas.
2. Sama, or devotional music, was central to the Chishti order.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'Both 1 and 2', 'D', 'Sufism was organised into silsilas (orders), and Sama (devotional music) was central to the Chishtis.', 5),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-bhakti-and-sufi-movements-q07', 'upsc-medieval-history-bhakti-and-sufi-movements', 'The Bhakti saint Chaitanya is chiefly associated with which region?', 'Bengal', 'Awadh', 'Rajasthan', 'Maharashtra', 'A', 'Chaitanya Mahaprabhu spread Krishna devotion in Bengal and Odisha.', 6),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-bhakti-and-sufi-movements-q08', 'upsc-medieval-history-bhakti-and-sufi-movements', 'The poet and musician closely associated with Nizamuddin Auliya was:', 'Tulsidas', 'Kabir', 'Surdas', 'Amir Khusro', 'D', 'Amir Khusro, a disciple of Nizamuddin Auliya, contributed greatly to a composite Indo-Islamic culture.', 7),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-temple-architecture-q01', 'upsc-art-and-culture-temple-architecture', 'The curvilinear shikhara is the defining feature of which temple style?', 'Nagara', 'Dravida', 'Vesara', 'Kalinga only', 'A', 'The Nagara style of north India is marked by a curvilinear shikhara and lacks boundary walls.', 0),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-temple-architecture-q02', 'upsc-art-and-culture-temple-architecture', 'The gopuram, a towering gateway, is a characteristic feature of which style?', 'Nagara', 'Dravida', 'Vesara', 'Bengal terracotta', 'B', 'The Dravida temple of south India is enclosed by walls with a gopuram gateway tower.', 1),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-temple-architecture-q03', 'upsc-art-and-culture-temple-architecture', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Brihadeshwara Temple at Thanjavur was built by the Cholas.
2. The Kandariya Mahadeva at Khajuraho is a Nagara temple.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'B', 'The Chola Brihadeshwara Temple is Dravida; Khajuraho''s Kandariya Mahadeva is a Nagara temple.', 2),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-temple-architecture-q04', 'upsc-art-and-culture-temple-architecture', 'In temple architecture, the ''garbhagriha'' is the:', 'Assembly hall', 'Circumambulatory path', 'Sanctum housing the deity', 'Gateway tower', 'C', 'The garbhagriha is the sanctum sanctorum that houses the main deity; the mandapa is the assembly hall.', 3),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-temple-architecture-q05', 'upsc-art-and-culture-temple-architecture', 'The monolithic Kailasa Temple at Ellora was carved by which dynasty?', 'Cholas', 'Rashtrakutas', 'Pallavas', 'Hoysalas', 'B', 'The Rashtrakutas carved the monolithic Kailasa Temple at Ellora from top to bottom.', 4),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-temple-architecture-q06', 'upsc-art-and-culture-temple-architecture', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Vesara style is a hybrid associated with the Chalukyas and Hoysalas.
2. The shore temple and rathas at Mahabalipuram were built by the Pallavas.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'Vesara is a hybrid style of the Chalukyas and Hoysalas; Mahabalipuram''s monuments are Pallava works.', 5),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-temple-architecture-q07', 'upsc-art-and-culture-temple-architecture', 'The Sun Temple at Konark is an example of which architectural style?', 'Nagara', 'Vesara', 'Dravida', 'Indo-Saracenic', 'A', 'The Sun Temple at Konark is a famous Nagara-style temple in Odisha.', 6),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-temple-architecture-q08', 'upsc-art-and-culture-temple-architecture', 'The amalaka and kalasha typically crown the tower of which temple style?', 'Cave temples', 'Dravida', 'Vesara', 'Nagara', 'D', 'The amalaka and kalasha crown the shikhara of a Nagara-style temple.', 7),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-classical-dance-forms-q01', 'upsc-art-and-culture-classical-dance-forms', 'How many dance forms are officially recognised as classical in India?', 'Six', 'Seven', 'Nine', 'Eight', 'D', 'India recognises eight classical dance forms, each rooted in Bharata''s Natya Shastra.', 0),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-classical-dance-forms-q02', 'upsc-art-and-culture-classical-dance-forms', 'Which classical dance form originates from Kerala and uses elaborate make-up and masks?', 'Kuchipudi', 'Kathakali', 'Odissi', 'Manipuri', 'B', 'Kathakali of Kerala uses elaborate make-up and masks to depict episodes from the epics.', 1),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-classical-dance-forms-q03', 'upsc-art-and-culture-classical-dance-forms', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Bharatanatyam is the oldest classical dance and originated in temples.
2. Kathak shows strong Persian and Mughal influence.
Which is/are correct?', 'Neither 1 nor 2', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'C', 'Bharatanatyam is the oldest temple dance, and Kathak carries strong Persian and Mughal influence.', 2),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-classical-dance-forms-q04', 'upsc-art-and-culture-classical-dance-forms', 'Sattriya, a classical dance form, originated in which state?', 'Odisha', 'Manipur', 'Assam', 'Tamil Nadu', 'C', 'Sattriya originated in Assam and was founded by the Vaishnavite saint Sankaradeva.', 3),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-classical-dance-forms-q05', 'upsc-art-and-culture-classical-dance-forms', 'Mohiniyattam, a solo female dance embodying Lasya grace, belongs to:', 'Odisha', 'Andhra Pradesh', 'Kerala', 'Karnataka', 'C', 'Mohiniyattam is a graceful solo female dance form from Kerala embodying the Lasya aspect.', 4),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-classical-dance-forms-q06', 'upsc-art-and-culture-classical-dance-forms', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Tandava is the vigorous, masculine aspect of dance.
2. Lasya is the graceful, feminine aspect of dance.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', '1 only', 'A', 'Tandava is the vigorous masculine aspect and Lasya the graceful feminine aspect of dance.', 5),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-classical-dance-forms-q07', 'upsc-art-and-culture-classical-dance-forms', 'The foundational treatise on Indian performing arts is the:', 'Abhinaya Darpana only', 'Arthashastra', 'Sangeet Ratnakara', 'Natya Shastra', 'D', 'Bharata''s Natya Shastra is the foundational treatise underpinning India''s classical dance forms.', 6),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-classical-dance-forms-q08', 'upsc-art-and-culture-classical-dance-forms', 'Manipuri dance is best known for its gentle devotional movements linked to:', 'Mughal courts', 'Tandava', 'The devadasi tradition', 'Raslila', 'D', 'Manipuri dance is known for its gentle, devotional movements linked to the Raslila of Krishna.', 7),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-indian-painting-schools-q01', 'upsc-art-and-culture-indian-painting-schools', 'The Ajanta cave murals were executed primarily in which technique?', 'Tempera', 'Watercolour wash', 'Oil painting', 'Fresco buono', 'A', 'The Buddhist murals of Ajanta were painted in the tempera technique.', 0),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-indian-painting-schools-q02', 'upsc-art-and-culture-indian-painting-schools', 'The famous ''Bani Thani'' portrait belongs to which school of painting?', 'Pahari (Kangra)', 'Mughal', 'Deccan', 'Kishangarh', 'D', 'The Bani Thani portrait is the signature work of the Kishangarh school of Rajasthani painting.', 1),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-indian-painting-schools-q03', 'upsc-art-and-culture-indian-painting-schools', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Madhubani painting originates from Bihar.
2. Warli painting uses white figures on a mud background.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'Madhubani (Mithila) painting is from Bihar; Warli painting uses white figures on a mud background.', 2),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-indian-painting-schools-q04', 'upsc-art-and-culture-indian-painting-schools', 'Mughal painting reached its zenith under which emperor?', 'Jahangir', 'Akbar', 'Shah Jahan', 'Humayun', 'A', 'Mughal painting, blending Persian technique with Indian themes, peaked under Jahangir.', 3),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-indian-painting-schools-q05', 'upsc-art-and-culture-indian-painting-schools', 'Pattachitra, a cloth-based scroll painting, is traditionally associated with:', 'Maharashtra', 'Bihar', 'Odisha and Bengal', 'Rajasthan', 'C', 'Pattachitra is a cloth-based scroll painting tradition of Odisha and Bengal.', 4),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-indian-painting-schools-q06', 'upsc-art-and-culture-indian-painting-schools', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Bengal School was led by Abanindranath Tagore.
2. It revived Indian themes against Western academic art.
Which is/are correct?', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', '1 only', 'B', 'Abanindranath Tagore led the Bengal School, which revived Indian themes against Western academic art.', 5),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-indian-painting-schools-q07', 'upsc-art-and-culture-indian-painting-schools', 'Which of the following is a Pahari school of miniature painting?', 'Kangra', 'Bijapur', 'Bundi', 'Mewar', 'A', 'Kangra and Basohli are Pahari schools; Bundi and Mewar are Rajasthani and Bijapur is Deccan.', 6),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-indian-painting-schools-q08', 'upsc-art-and-culture-indian-painting-schools', 'The Deccan school of miniature painting flourished at which centres?', 'Kangra and Basohli', 'Mewar and Bundi', 'Mithila and Tanjore', 'Bijapur and Golconda', 'D', 'The Deccan school flourished at Bijapur and Golconda.', 7),
  ('upsc-geography-indian-physiography-and-rivers-q01', 'upsc-geography-indian-physiography-and-rivers', 'The largest peninsular river of India, called the ''Dakshin Ganga'', is the:', 'Mahanadi', 'Kaveri', 'Krishna', 'Godavari', 'D', 'The Godavari is the largest peninsular river and is known as the Dakshin Ganga.', 0),
  ('upsc-geography-indian-physiography-and-rivers-q02', 'upsc-geography-indian-physiography-and-rivers', 'Which two rivers flow westward through rift valleys into the Arabian Sea?', 'Godavari and Krishna', 'Ganga and Yamuna', 'Narmada and Tapi', 'Mahanadi and Kaveri', 'C', 'The Narmada and Tapi flow westward through rift valleys into the Arabian Sea.', 1),
  ('upsc-geography-indian-physiography-and-rivers-q03', 'upsc-geography-indian-physiography-and-rivers', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Indus and Brahmaputra are antecedent rivers.
2. They are older than the Himalayas.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'The Indus and Brahmaputra are antecedent rivers older than the Himalayas through which they cut.', 2),
  ('upsc-geography-indian-physiography-and-rivers-q04', 'upsc-geography-indian-physiography-and-rivers', 'The highest peak of peninsular India is:', 'K2 (Godwin Austen)', 'Anamudi', 'Doda Betta', 'Mahendragiri', 'B', 'Anamudi, in the Western Ghats, is the highest peak of peninsular India.', 3),
  ('upsc-geography-indian-physiography-and-rivers-q05', 'upsc-geography-indian-physiography-and-rivers', 'The three parallel ranges of the Himalayas from north to south are:', 'Himadri, Himachal, Shiwaliks', 'Shiwaliks, Himachal, Himadri', 'Himachal, Himadri, Shiwaliks', 'Himadri, Shiwaliks, Himachal', 'A', 'From north to south the ranges are the Himadri (Greater), Himachal (Lesser) and Shiwaliks (Outer).', 4),
  ('upsc-geography-indian-physiography-and-rivers-q06', 'upsc-geography-indian-physiography-and-rivers', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Peninsular Plateau is the oldest landmass made of Gondwana rocks.
2. The Western Ghats are continuous and higher than the Eastern Ghats.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'Both 1 and 2', 'D', 'The Peninsular Plateau is the oldest Gondwana landmass, and the Western Ghats are continuous and higher.', 5),
  ('upsc-geography-indian-physiography-and-rivers-q07', 'upsc-geography-indian-physiography-and-rivers', 'The highest peak located within India is:', 'Mount Everest', 'Kanchenjunga', 'K2 (Godwin Austen)', 'Nanda Devi', 'C', 'K2, also called Godwin Austen, is the highest peak in India (in the Karakoram range).', 6),
  ('upsc-geography-indian-physiography-and-rivers-q08', 'upsc-geography-indian-physiography-and-rivers', 'Himalayan rivers are generally described as perennial because they are fed by:', 'Only the monsoon', 'Both glaciers and rainfall', 'Only groundwater', 'Only lakes', 'B', 'Himalayan rivers are perennial because they receive water from both melting glaciers and rainfall.', 7),
  ('upsc-geography-soils-and-agriculture-q01', 'upsc-geography-soils-and-agriculture', 'Black soil (regur) is especially suited to the cultivation of:', 'Tea', 'Coffee', 'Rice', 'Cotton', 'D', 'Black soil, or regur, retains moisture well and is ideal for cotton, hence ''black cotton soil''.', 0),
  ('upsc-geography-soils-and-agriculture-q02', 'upsc-geography-soils-and-agriculture', 'In the alluvial soils of India, the older alluvium is known as:', 'Khadar', 'Bhangar', 'Regur', 'Laterite', 'B', 'Bhangar is old alluvium while khadar is the newer, more fertile alluvium.', 1),
  ('upsc-geography-soils-and-agriculture-q03', 'upsc-geography-soils-and-agriculture', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Kharif crops are sown in June-July.
2. Rabi crops include wheat and gram.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'Kharif crops are sown in June-July; rabi crops such as wheat and gram are sown in winter.', 2),
  ('upsc-geography-soils-and-agriculture-q04', 'upsc-geography-soils-and-agriculture', 'The White Revolution in India is associated with:', 'Foodgrains', 'Oilseeds', 'Milk production', 'Fisheries', 'C', 'The White Revolution (Operation Flood) under Verghese Kurien boosted milk production.', 3),
  ('upsc-geography-soils-and-agriculture-q05', 'upsc-geography-soils-and-agriculture', 'Laterite soil, formed by leaching, is best suited to which crops?', 'Wheat and sugarcane', 'Tea, coffee and cashew', 'Mustard and pulses', 'Cotton and gram', 'B', 'Leached, acidic laterite soil suits plantation crops like tea, coffee and cashew.', 4),
  ('upsc-geography-soils-and-agriculture-q06', 'upsc-geography-soils-and-agriculture', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Green Revolution was associated with M.S. Swaminathan and Norman Borlaug.
2. Alluvial soil covers about 40% of India''s land.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'Both 1 and 2', 'D', 'Swaminathan and Borlaug led the Green Revolution; alluvial soil covers roughly 40% of India''s land.', 5),
  ('upsc-geography-soils-and-agriculture-q07', 'upsc-geography-soils-and-agriculture', 'Which cropping season corresponds to the short summer period?', 'Kharif', 'Zaid', 'Rabi', 'Bhangar', 'B', 'The Zaid season is the short summer cropping period for crops like watermelon and cucumber.', 6),
  ('upsc-geography-soils-and-agriculture-q08', 'upsc-geography-soils-and-agriculture', 'The Blue Revolution in India refers to development in:', 'Oilseeds', 'Milk', 'Fisheries', 'Foodgrains', 'C', 'The Blue Revolution refers to the development of fisheries and aquaculture.', 7),
  ('upsc-geography-world-geography-landforms-q01', 'upsc-geography-world-geography-landforms', 'The theory of Continental Drift was proposed by:', 'Alfred Wegener', 'Charles Lyell', 'James Hutton', 'Harry Hess', 'A', 'Alfred Wegener proposed the Continental Drift theory, a precursor to plate tectonics.', 0),
  ('upsc-geography-world-geography-landforms-q02', 'upsc-geography-world-geography-landforms', 'Mid-ocean ridges and rift valleys are typically formed at which plate boundary?', 'Convergent', 'Subduction', 'Transform', 'Divergent', 'D', 'Divergent boundaries, where plates move apart, create mid-ocean ridges and rift valleys.', 1),
  ('upsc-geography-world-geography-landforms-q03', 'upsc-geography-world-geography-landforms', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Himalayas formed by the convergence of the Indian and Eurasian plates.
2. The Pacific Ring of Fire hosts about two-thirds of the world''s active volcanoes.
Which is/are correct?', 'Neither 1 nor 2', '2 only', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'D', 'The Himalayas arose from Indian-Eurasian convergence; the Ring of Fire holds about two-thirds of active volcanoes.', 2),
  ('upsc-geography-world-geography-landforms-q04', 'upsc-geography-world-geography-landforms', 'The San Andreas Fault is a classic example of which type of plate boundary?', 'Transform', 'Divergent', 'Convergent', 'Continental', 'A', 'The San Andreas Fault is a transform boundary where plates slide past one another, causing earthquakes.', 3),
  ('upsc-geography-world-geography-landforms-q05', 'upsc-geography-world-geography-landforms', 'The highest plateau in the world is the:', 'Colorado Plateau', 'Deccan Plateau', 'Tibetan Plateau', 'Ethiopian Plateau', 'C', 'The Tibetan Plateau is the highest plateau in the world.', 4),
  ('upsc-geography-world-geography-landforms-q06', 'upsc-geography-world-geography-landforms', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Block mountains are formed by horst and graben structures.
2. The Himalayas and Andes are examples of fold mountains.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'Both 1 and 2', 'D', 'Block mountains arise from horst-and-graben faulting; the Himalayas and Andes are fold mountains.', 5),
  ('upsc-geography-world-geography-landforms-q07', 'upsc-geography-world-geography-landforms', 'Forces originating from within the Earth that shape landforms are called:', 'Exogenic forces', 'Aeolian forces', 'Gradational forces', 'Endogenic forces', 'D', 'Endogenic (internal) forces such as tectonics build landforms; exogenic forces wear them down.', 6),
  ('upsc-geography-world-geography-landforms-q08', 'upsc-geography-world-geography-landforms', 'The outermost layer of the Earth, broken into tectonic plates, is the:', 'Lithosphere', 'Mantle', 'Outer core', 'Asthenosphere', 'A', 'The lithosphere is the rigid outer layer of the Earth that is broken into tectonic plates.', 7),
  ('upsc-economy-national-income-and-gdp-q01', 'upsc-economy-national-income-and-gdp', 'Gross Domestic Product (GDP) measures the value of final goods and services produced:', 'Within a country''s borders', 'Only in the manufacturing sector', 'By a country''s nationals worldwide', 'After deducting depreciation', 'A', 'GDP is the value of all final goods and services produced within a country''s borders in a year.', 0),
  ('upsc-economy-national-income-and-gdp-q02', 'upsc-economy-national-income-and-gdp', 'Gross National Product (GNP) is equal to:', 'GDP plus depreciation', 'GDP minus depreciation', 'GDP plus net factor income from abroad', 'NNP plus taxes', 'C', 'GNP equals GDP plus net factor income from abroad (NFIA).', 1),
  ('upsc-economy-national-income-and-gdp-q03', 'upsc-economy-national-income-and-gdp', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Nominal GDP is calculated at current prices.
2. Real GDP is calculated at constant base-year prices.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'Both 1 and 2', 'D', 'Nominal GDP uses current prices, while real GDP uses constant base-year prices.', 2),
  ('upsc-economy-national-income-and-gdp-q04', 'upsc-economy-national-income-and-gdp', 'The current base year for India''s GDP estimates is:', '2004-05', '2015-16', '2011-12', '2020-21', 'C', 'India''s GDP series uses 2011-12 as the base year, with figures released by the NSO under MoSPI.', 3),
  ('upsc-economy-national-income-and-gdp-q05', 'upsc-economy-national-income-and-gdp', 'The GDP deflator is calculated as:', '(Nominal GDP / Real GDP) x 100', 'Nominal GDP minus Real GDP', '(Real GDP / Nominal GDP) x 100', 'GDP minus depreciation', 'A', 'The GDP deflator equals Nominal GDP divided by Real GDP, multiplied by 100.', 4),
  ('upsc-economy-national-income-and-gdp-q06', 'upsc-economy-national-income-and-gdp', 'Consider the following statements:
1. NNP at factor cost is termed the National Income.
2. Per capita income equals National Income divided by population.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'NNP at factor cost is the National Income, and per capita income is National Income divided by population.', 5),
  ('upsc-economy-national-income-and-gdp-q07', 'upsc-economy-national-income-and-gdp', 'Net Domestic Product (NDP) is obtained by:', 'Adding NFIA to GDP', 'Subtracting taxes from GNP', 'Adding depreciation to GDP', 'Subtracting depreciation from GDP', 'D', 'NDP equals GDP minus depreciation.', 6),
  ('upsc-economy-national-income-and-gdp-q08', 'upsc-economy-national-income-and-gdp', 'Which of the following is NOT one of the three methods of measuring national income?', 'Production (value-added) method', 'Income method', 'Expenditure method', 'Depreciation method', 'D', 'National income is measured by the production, income and expenditure methods, not a ''depreciation method''.', 7),
  ('upsc-economy-banking-system-and-rbi-q01', 'upsc-economy-banking-system-and-rbi', 'In which year was the Reserve Bank of India nationalised?', '1935', '1947', '1949', '1969', 'C', 'The RBI was established in 1935 and nationalised in 1949.', 0),
  ('upsc-economy-banking-system-and-rbi-q02', 'upsc-economy-banking-system-and-rbi', 'The ''repo rate'' is the rate at which:', 'Banks lend to the RBI', 'The RBI lends to commercial banks', 'Banks lend to each other', 'The government borrows from the public', 'B', 'The repo rate is the rate at which the RBI lends short-term funds to commercial banks.', 1),
  ('upsc-economy-banking-system-and-rbi-q03', 'upsc-economy-banking-system-and-rbi', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The RBI is the sole issuer of currency except the one-rupee note and coins.
2. The RBI is the lender of last resort to banks.
Which is/are correct?', 'Neither 1 nor 2', '2 only', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'D', 'The RBI issues currency except the one-rupee note and coins, and acts as lender of last resort.', 2),
  ('upsc-economy-banking-system-and-rbi-q04', 'upsc-economy-banking-system-and-rbi', 'An asset is classified as a Non-Performing Asset (NPA) if interest or principal is overdue for:', '30 days', '60 days', '180 days', '90 days', 'D', 'A loan becomes an NPA when interest or principal remains overdue for 90 days.', 3),
  ('upsc-economy-banking-system-and-rbi-q05', 'upsc-economy-banking-system-and-rbi', 'The one-rupee note and coins in India are issued by:', 'The Ministry of Finance', 'The Reserve Bank of India', 'The State Bank of India', 'NABARD', 'A', 'The one-rupee note and coins are issued by the Ministry of Finance, not the RBI.', 4),
  ('upsc-economy-banking-system-and-rbi-q06', 'upsc-economy-banking-system-and-rbi', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The SLR is capped at 40%.
2. Scheduled commercial banks are listed in the Second Schedule of the RBI Act.
Which is/are correct?', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', '1 only', 'B', 'SLR is capped at 40% and scheduled commercial banks are listed in the Second Schedule of the RBI Act.', 5),
  ('upsc-economy-banking-system-and-rbi-q07', 'upsc-economy-banking-system-and-rbi', 'Which of the following is true of Payments Banks in India?', 'They cannot lend or issue credit cards', 'They can give long-term loans', 'They can issue credit cards', 'They function only in rural areas', 'A', 'Payments Banks accept small deposits but cannot lend or issue credit cards.', 6),
  ('upsc-economy-banking-system-and-rbi-q08', 'upsc-economy-banking-system-and-rbi', 'The Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code (IBC) was enacted in which year?', '2016', '2013', '2014', '2018', 'A', 'The Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code was enacted in 2016 to speed up resolution of bad loans.', 7),
  ('upsc-economy-union-budget-and-fiscal-policy-q01', 'upsc-economy-union-budget-and-fiscal-policy', 'The Union Budget is presented as the ''Annual Financial Statement'' under which Article?', 'Article 280', 'Article 110', 'Article 266', 'Article 112', 'D', 'Article 112 provides for the Annual Financial Statement, that is, the Union Budget.', 0),
  ('upsc-economy-union-budget-and-fiscal-policy-q02', 'upsc-economy-union-budget-and-fiscal-policy', 'The Fiscal Deficit is best defined as:', 'Total Expenditure minus Total Receipts excluding borrowings', 'Revenue Expenditure minus Revenue Receipts', 'Fiscal Deficit minus Interest Payments', 'Capital Receipts minus Capital Expenditure', 'A', 'The Fiscal Deficit equals total expenditure minus total receipts excluding borrowings, indicating borrowing needs.', 1),
  ('upsc-economy-union-budget-and-fiscal-policy-q03', 'upsc-economy-union-budget-and-fiscal-policy', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Primary Deficit equals the Fiscal Deficit minus interest payments.
2. The FRBM Act was enacted in 2003.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'The Primary Deficit is the Fiscal Deficit minus interest payments; the FRBM Act was passed in 2003.', 2),
  ('upsc-economy-union-budget-and-fiscal-policy-q04', 'upsc-economy-union-budget-and-fiscal-policy', 'The Goods and Services Tax (GST) was launched in India on:', '1 July 2017', '26 January 2017', '1 January 2018', '1 April 2016', 'A', 'GST, a destination-based tax, was launched on 1 July 2017 and is governed by the GST Council.', 3),
  ('upsc-economy-union-budget-and-fiscal-policy-q05', 'upsc-economy-union-budget-and-fiscal-policy', 'The GST Council is a constitutional body created under which Article?', 'Article 112', 'Article 279A', 'Article 110', 'Article 266', 'B', 'The GST Council is established under Article 279A of the Constitution.', 4),
  ('upsc-economy-union-budget-and-fiscal-policy-q06', 'upsc-economy-union-budget-and-fiscal-policy', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Direct taxes are progressive.
2. Indirect taxes such as GST are regressive.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'Both 1 and 2', 'D', 'Direct taxes like income tax are progressive, while indirect taxes such as GST are regressive.', 5),
  ('upsc-economy-union-budget-and-fiscal-policy-q07', 'upsc-economy-union-budget-and-fiscal-policy', 'All revenues received by the Government of India are credited to the:', 'Contingency Fund', 'Public Account', 'Consolidated Fund of India', 'Capital Account', 'C', 'The Consolidated Fund of India (Article 266) holds all government revenues; withdrawals need parliamentary approval.', 6),
  ('upsc-economy-union-budget-and-fiscal-policy-q08', 'upsc-economy-union-budget-and-fiscal-policy', 'Which of the following is a revenue receipt of the government?', 'Disinvestment proceeds', 'Tax revenue', 'Borrowings', 'Recovery of loans', 'B', 'Tax revenue is a non-debt-creating revenue receipt; borrowings and disinvestment are capital receipts.', 7),
  ('upsc-environment-biodiversity-and-conservation-q01', 'upsc-environment-biodiversity-and-conservation', 'How many biodiversity hotspots are located in India?', 'Two', 'Three', 'Four', 'Six', 'C', 'India has four biodiversity hotspots: the Himalayas, Western Ghats, Indo-Burma and Sundaland.', 0),
  ('upsc-environment-biodiversity-and-conservation-q02', 'upsc-environment-biodiversity-and-conservation', 'Conservation of species within their natural habitat is known as:', 'Ex-situ conservation', 'In-situ conservation', 'Cryopreservation', 'Captive breeding', 'B', 'In-situ conservation protects species in their natural habitat, such as national parks and sanctuaries.', 1),
  ('upsc-environment-biodiversity-and-conservation-q03', 'upsc-environment-biodiversity-and-conservation', 'Consider the following statements:
1. National Parks allow no human activity.
2. Wildlife Sanctuaries permit some regulated activity.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '1 only', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'A', 'National Parks prohibit human activity while Sanctuaries permit certain regulated activities.', 2),
  ('upsc-environment-biodiversity-and-conservation-q04', 'upsc-environment-biodiversity-and-conservation', 'Project Tiger was launched in which year?', '1972', '1992', '1985', '1973', 'D', 'Project Tiger was launched in 1973; Project Elephant followed in 1992.', 3),
  ('upsc-environment-biodiversity-and-conservation-q05', 'upsc-environment-biodiversity-and-conservation', 'The Convention on Biological Diversity (CBD) was adopted at which summit?', 'Stockholm Conference 1972', 'Johannesburg Summit 2002', 'Rio Earth Summit 1992', 'Paris Summit 2015', 'C', 'The CBD was adopted at the Rio Earth Summit in 1992.', 4),
  ('upsc-environment-biodiversity-and-conservation-q06', 'upsc-environment-biodiversity-and-conservation', 'Consider the following statements:
1. India is one of 17 megadiverse countries.
2. Biosphere Reserves have core, buffer and transition zones.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'India is among 17 megadiverse nations, and Biosphere Reserves comprise core, buffer and transition zones.', 5),
  ('upsc-environment-biodiversity-and-conservation-q07', 'upsc-environment-biodiversity-and-conservation', 'Protected species in India are listed in the schedules of which Act?', 'Biological Diversity Act, 2002', 'Environment Protection Act, 1986', 'Forest Conservation Act, 1980', 'Wildlife (Protection) Act, 1972', 'D', 'The Wildlife (Protection) Act, 1972 lists protected species in its schedules.', 6),
  ('upsc-environment-biodiversity-and-conservation-q08', 'upsc-environment-biodiversity-and-conservation', 'Which international convention regulates trade in endangered species?', 'CBD', 'CITES', 'Ramsar Convention', 'UNFCCC', 'B', 'CITES regulates international trade in endangered species of wild fauna and flora.', 7),
  ('upsc-environment-climate-change-and-global-agreements-q01', 'upsc-environment-climate-change-and-global-agreements', 'The Paris Agreement (2015) aims to limit the rise in global average temperature to:', 'Below 3 degrees C', 'Below 4 degrees C', 'Exactly 2.5 degrees C', 'Well below 2 degrees C, pursuing 1.5 degrees C', 'D', 'The Paris Agreement seeks to keep warming well below 2 degrees C while pursuing 1.5 degrees C.', 0),
  ('upsc-environment-climate-change-and-global-agreements-q02', 'upsc-environment-climate-change-and-global-agreements', 'The Montreal Protocol (1987) was aimed at phasing out:', 'Greenhouse gases', 'Ozone-depleting substances', 'Fossil fuel subsidies', 'Plastic waste', 'B', 'The Montreal Protocol phased out ozone-depleting substances; its Kigali Amendment targets HFCs.', 1),
  ('upsc-environment-climate-change-and-global-agreements-q03', 'upsc-environment-climate-change-and-global-agreements', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The IPCC was set up in 1988 by WMO and UNEP.
2. The UNFCCC of 1992 is the parent climate treaty.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', '1 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'A', 'The IPCC was set up in 1988 by WMO and UNEP, and the 1992 UNFCCC is the parent climate treaty.', 2),
  ('upsc-environment-climate-change-and-global-agreements-q04', 'upsc-environment-climate-change-and-global-agreements', 'India has set a target of achieving net zero emissions by:', '2050', '2060', '2047', '2070', 'D', 'India targets net zero emissions by 2070, following the principle of CBDR.', 3),
  ('upsc-environment-climate-change-and-global-agreements-q05', 'upsc-environment-climate-change-and-global-agreements', 'The Kyoto Protocol of 1997 set binding emission targets primarily for:', 'Developing nations', 'Only island nations', 'All UN members equally', 'Developed nations', 'D', 'The Kyoto Protocol set binding greenhouse gas targets for developed nations.', 4),
  ('upsc-environment-climate-change-and-global-agreements-q06', 'upsc-environment-climate-change-and-global-agreements', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Methane is mainly emitted by livestock, paddy and landfills.
2. The Paris Agreement operates through Nationally Determined Contributions.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'B', 'Methane comes from livestock, paddy and landfills; the Paris Agreement works through NDCs.', 5),
  ('upsc-environment-climate-change-and-global-agreements-q07', 'upsc-environment-climate-change-and-global-agreements', 'Parties to the UNFCCC meet annually at the:', 'G20 Summit', 'General Assembly', 'Security Council', 'Conference of the Parties (COP)', 'D', 'Parties to the UNFCCC meet annually at the Conference of the Parties (COP).', 6),
  ('upsc-environment-climate-change-and-global-agreements-q08', 'upsc-environment-climate-change-and-global-agreements', 'India''s climate missions are coordinated under which national framework?', 'NAPCC', 'NITI Aayog', 'FRBM', 'NDB', 'A', 'India''s climate missions operate under the National Action Plan on Climate Change (NAPCC).', 7),
  ('upsc-environment-ecosystems-and-food-chains-q01', 'upsc-environment-ecosystems-and-food-chains', 'In an ecosystem, green plants are classified as:', 'Primary consumers', 'Decomposers', 'Producers', 'Secondary consumers', 'C', 'Green plants are autotrophic producers that fix energy at the base of the food chain.', 0),
  ('upsc-environment-ecosystems-and-food-chains-q02', 'upsc-environment-ecosystems-and-food-chains', 'According to Lindeman''s 10% law, the energy transferred to the next trophic level is about:', '10%', '1%', '50%', '90%', 'A', 'Lindeman''s 10% law states that only about 10% of energy is transferred to the next trophic level.', 1),
  ('upsc-environment-ecosystems-and-food-chains-q03', 'upsc-environment-ecosystems-and-food-chains', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Energy flow in an ecosystem is unidirectional.
2. The pyramid of energy is always upright.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', '1 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'A', 'Energy flow is unidirectional and the energy pyramid is always upright.', 2),
  ('upsc-environment-ecosystems-and-food-chains-q04', 'upsc-environment-ecosystems-and-food-chains', 'Which of the following are decomposers in an ecosystem?', 'Bacteria and fungi', 'Carnivores', 'Herbivores', 'Green plants', 'A', 'Bacteria and fungi act as decomposers, breaking down dead organic matter.', 3),
  ('upsc-environment-ecosystems-and-food-chains-q05', 'upsc-environment-ecosystems-and-food-chains', 'An interconnected network of food chains is called a:', 'Ecological niche', 'Trophic level', 'Biome', 'Food web', 'D', 'A food web is an interconnected network of multiple food chains.', 4),
  ('upsc-environment-ecosystems-and-food-chains-q06', 'upsc-environment-ecosystems-and-food-chains', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Net Primary Productivity equals GPP minus respiration.
2. NPP is the energy available to consumers.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'NPP equals GPP minus respiration and represents the energy available to consumers.', 5),
  ('upsc-environment-ecosystems-and-food-chains-q07', 'upsc-environment-ecosystems-and-food-chains', 'Which of the following is an abiotic component of an ecosystem?', 'Herbivores', 'Decomposers', 'Producers', 'Sunlight', 'D', 'Sunlight, water, soil and temperature are abiotic (non-living) components of an ecosystem.', 6),
  ('upsc-environment-ecosystems-and-food-chains-q08', 'upsc-environment-ecosystems-and-food-chains', 'Herbivores in a food chain occupy the trophic level of:', 'Producers', 'Primary consumers', 'Secondary consumers', 'Decomposers', 'B', 'Herbivores feed on producers and so occupy the primary consumer trophic level.', 7),
  ('upsc-science-technology-space-technology-isro-q01', 'upsc-science-technology-space-technology-isro', 'Who is regarded as the father of the Indian space programme?', 'A.P.J. Abdul Kalam', 'Vikram Sarabhai', 'Satish Dhawan', 'Homi Bhabha', 'B', 'Vikram Sarabhai, under whom ISRO was founded in 1969, is the father of the Indian space programme.', 0),
  ('upsc-science-technology-space-technology-isro-q02', 'upsc-science-technology-space-technology-isro', 'India''s first satellite, launched in 1975, was named:', 'Bhaskara', 'Rohini', 'Aryabhata', 'INSAT-1A', 'C', 'Aryabhata, launched in 1975, was India''s first satellite.', 1),
  ('upsc-science-technology-space-technology-isro-q03', 'upsc-science-technology-space-technology-isro', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The PSLV is known as the workhorse of ISRO.
2. The GSLV uses an indigenous cryogenic upper stage.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'B', 'The PSLV is ISRO''s workhorse, and the GSLV uses an indigenous cryogenic upper stage.', 2),
  ('upsc-science-technology-space-technology-isro-q04', 'upsc-science-technology-space-technology-isro', 'Which Indian mission made India the first nation to reach Mars orbit on its first attempt?', 'Chandrayaan-1', 'Mangalyaan (Mars Orbiter Mission)', 'Aditya-L1', 'Gaganyaan', 'B', 'Mangalyaan (2013) made India the first nation to reach Mars orbit on its first attempt.', 3),
  ('upsc-science-technology-space-technology-isro-q05', 'upsc-science-technology-space-technology-isro', 'Chandrayaan-3 (2023) is notable for soft-landing near the Moon''s:', 'North pole', 'South pole', 'Equator', 'Far side centre', 'B', 'Chandrayaan-3 soft-landed near the lunar south pole in 2023.', 4),
  ('upsc-science-technology-space-technology-isro-q06', 'upsc-science-technology-space-technology-isro', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Chandrayaan-1 discovered water molecules on the Moon.
2. NavIC is India''s regional satellite navigation system.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '1 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', '2 only', 'A', 'Chandrayaan-1 found water molecules on the Moon, and NavIC (IRNSS) is India''s regional navigation system.', 5),
  ('upsc-science-technology-space-technology-isro-q07', 'upsc-science-technology-space-technology-isro', 'The Aditya-L1 mission is designed to study the:', 'Sun', 'Mars', 'Moon', 'Venus', 'A', 'Aditya-L1 studies the Sun from the L1 Lagrange point.', 6),
  ('upsc-science-technology-space-technology-isro-q08', 'upsc-science-technology-space-technology-isro', 'Gaganyaan is India''s planned mission for:', 'A Mars rover', 'Its first crewed spaceflight', 'A lunar sample return', 'An asteroid mission', 'B', 'Gaganyaan aims to achieve India''s first crewed spaceflight.', 7),
  ('upsc-science-technology-biotechnology-basics-q01', 'upsc-science-technology-biotechnology-basics', 'Which enzymes are used to cut DNA at specific recognition sites?', 'Polymerases', 'DNA ligases', 'Restriction enzymes', 'Helicases', 'C', 'Restriction enzymes cut DNA at specific sequences, a key tool in genetic engineering.', 0),
  ('upsc-science-technology-biotechnology-basics-q02', 'upsc-science-technology-biotechnology-basics', 'The technique used to amplify copies of a DNA segment is:', 'Electrophoresis', 'Chromatography', 'Centrifugation', 'PCR (Polymerase Chain Reaction)', 'D', 'PCR (Polymerase Chain Reaction) amplifies copies of a specific DNA segment.', 1),
  ('upsc-science-technology-biotechnology-basics-q03', 'upsc-science-technology-biotechnology-basics', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Bt cotton is India''s only approved GM crop for commercial cultivation.
2. Golden Rice is engineered to be rich in Vitamin A.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'Bt cotton is India''s only approved commercial GM crop, and Golden Rice is engineered for Vitamin A.', 2),
  ('upsc-science-technology-biotechnology-basics-q04', 'upsc-science-technology-biotechnology-basics', 'Which body in India approves the release of genetically modified organisms?', 'ICMR', 'GEAC', 'DBT', 'CSIR', 'B', 'The Genetic Engineering Appraisal Committee (GEAC) under the MoEFCC approves GM organisms.', 3),
  ('upsc-science-technology-biotechnology-basics-q05', 'upsc-science-technology-biotechnology-basics', 'The revolutionary precise gene-editing tool widely used in biotechnology is:', 'PCR', 'Gel electrophoresis', 'CRISPR-Cas9', 'Plasmid cloning', 'C', 'CRISPR-Cas9 is a revolutionary tool for precise gene editing.', 4),
  ('upsc-science-technology-biotechnology-basics-q06', 'upsc-science-technology-biotechnology-basics', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Plasmids are used as vectors to carry genes into cells.
2. Bt cotton resists bollworm pests.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', '2 only', 'B', 'Plasmids serve as vectors carrying genes into cells, and Bt cotton resists bollworm pests.', 5),
  ('upsc-science-technology-biotechnology-basics-q07', 'upsc-science-technology-biotechnology-basics', 'The insertion, deletion or modification of genes using recombinant DNA is called:', 'Tissue culture', 'Hybridisation', 'Fermentation', 'Genetic engineering', 'D', 'Genetic engineering modifies genes using recombinant DNA technology.', 6),
  ('upsc-science-technology-biotechnology-basics-q08', 'upsc-science-technology-biotechnology-basics', 'Which of the following is commonly produced using biotechnology?', 'Steel', 'Cement', 'Petroleum', 'Insulin', 'D', 'Insulin, vaccines and monoclonal antibodies are produced using biotechnology.', 7),
  ('upsc-science-technology-defence-technology-q01', 'upsc-science-technology-defence-technology', 'The Defence Research and Development Organisation (DRDO) was established in:', '1947', '1974', '1969', '1958', 'D', 'DRDO was established in 1958 to make India''s armed forces self-reliant in technology.', 0),
  ('upsc-science-technology-defence-technology-q02', 'upsc-science-technology-defence-technology', 'The Integrated Guided Missile Development Programme (IGMDP) was led by:', 'Homi Bhabha', 'A.P.J. Abdul Kalam', 'Vikram Sarabhai', 'Satish Dhawan', 'B', 'Dr. A.P.J. Abdul Kalam led the IGMDP, earning the title ''Missile Man of India''.', 1),
  ('upsc-science-technology-defence-technology-q03', 'upsc-science-technology-defence-technology', 'Consider the following statements:
1. BrahMos is an India-Russia joint venture cruise missile.
2. Akash is a surface-to-air missile.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'BrahMos is an India-Russia supersonic cruise missile and Akash is a surface-to-air missile.', 2),
  ('upsc-science-technology-defence-technology-q04', 'upsc-science-technology-defence-technology', 'Tejas is India''s indigenous:', 'Light Combat Aircraft', 'Main battle tank', 'Nuclear submarine', 'Aircraft carrier', 'A', 'Tejas is India''s indigenous Light Combat Aircraft (LCA).', 3),
  ('upsc-science-technology-defence-technology-q05', 'upsc-science-technology-defence-technology', 'INS Arihant is significant as India''s:', 'First aircraft carrier', 'Largest destroyer', 'First frigate', 'First nuclear-powered submarine', 'D', 'INS Arihant is India''s first indigenous nuclear-powered ballistic missile submarine, completing the nuclear triad.', 4),
  ('upsc-science-technology-defence-technology-q06', 'upsc-science-technology-defence-technology', 'Consider the following statements:
1. India follows a No First Use nuclear doctrine.
2. INS Vikrant is India''s first indigenous aircraft carrier.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'C', 'India follows a No First Use doctrine, and INS Vikrant is its first indigenous aircraft carrier.', 5),
  ('upsc-science-technology-defence-technology-q07', 'upsc-science-technology-defence-technology', 'The Agni series of missiles are classified as:', 'Surface-to-air missiles', 'Anti-tank missiles', 'Cruise missiles', 'Surface-to-surface ballistic missiles', 'D', 'Agni missiles are surface-to-surface ballistic missiles.', 6),
  ('upsc-science-technology-defence-technology-q08', 'upsc-science-technology-defence-technology', 'The Nag missile developed by DRDO is a:', 'Surface-to-air missile', 'Anti-tank guided missile', 'Intercontinental ballistic missile', 'Cruise missile', 'B', 'The Nag is an anti-tank guided missile developed under the IGMDP.', 7),
  ('upsc-international-relations-india-and-its-neighbours-q01', 'upsc-international-relations-india-and-its-neighbours', 'With which country does India share its longest land border?', 'Bangladesh', 'Pakistan', 'Nepal', 'China', 'A', 'India shares its longest land border with Bangladesh.', 0),
  ('upsc-international-relations-india-and-its-neighbours-q02', 'upsc-international-relations-india-and-its-neighbours', 'The boundary line between India and China in the eastern sector is the:', 'Radcliffe Line', 'Line of Control', 'Durand Line', 'McMahon Line', 'D', 'The McMahon Line demarcates the India-China boundary in the eastern sector.', 1),
  ('upsc-international-relations-india-and-its-neighbours-q03', 'upsc-international-relations-india-and-its-neighbours', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Chabahar Port is located in Iran.
2. It helps India reach Afghanistan and Central Asia bypassing Pakistan.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '1 only', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'A', 'The Chabahar Port in Iran lets India reach Afghanistan and Central Asia while bypassing Pakistan.', 2),
  ('upsc-international-relations-india-and-its-neighbours-q04', 'upsc-international-relations-india-and-its-neighbours', 'The ''SAGAR'' doctrine relates to India''s policy in which domain?', 'Cyber security', 'Space cooperation', 'Maritime security and growth', 'Trade tariffs', 'C', 'SAGAR (Security and Growth for All in the Region) guides India''s maritime policy in the Indian Ocean.', 3),
  ('upsc-international-relations-india-and-its-neighbours-q05', 'upsc-international-relations-india-and-its-neighbours', 'The Kalapani territorial dispute is between India and:', 'China', 'Bhutan', 'Myanmar', 'Nepal', 'D', 'The Kalapani dispute is a boundary issue between India and Nepal.', 4),
  ('upsc-international-relations-india-and-its-neighbours-q06', 'upsc-international-relations-india-and-its-neighbours', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Land Boundary Agreement with Bangladesh was implemented in 2015.
2. India and China are separated by the Line of Actual Control.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'Both 1 and 2', 'D', 'The India-Bangladesh Land Boundary Agreement took effect in 2015; India and China are divided by the LAC.', 5),
  ('upsc-international-relations-india-and-its-neighbours-q07', 'upsc-international-relations-india-and-its-neighbours', 'The Gujral Doctrine emphasised:', 'Non-reciprocal accommodation of smaller neighbours', 'Strict reciprocity with all neighbours', 'Military alliances in South Asia', 'Economic sanctions on rivals', 'A', 'The Gujral Doctrine emphasised non-reciprocal accommodation of India''s smaller neighbours.', 6),
  ('upsc-international-relations-india-and-its-neighbours-q08', 'upsc-international-relations-india-and-its-neighbours', 'India''s broad approach toward its immediate neighbours is captured by which policy?', 'Look East Policy', 'Indo-Pacific Strategy', 'Neighbourhood First Policy', 'Connect Central Asia Policy', 'C', 'India''s approach to its immediate neighbours is guided by the ''Neighbourhood First'' policy.', 7),
  ('upsc-international-relations-major-global-groupings-q01', 'upsc-international-relations-major-global-groupings', 'Which countries make up the QUAD grouping?', 'India, US, UK, France', 'India, China, Russia, Brazil', 'India, Japan, Israel, UAE', 'India, US, Japan, Australia', 'D', 'The QUAD comprises India, the United States, Japan and Australia.', 0),
  ('upsc-international-relations-major-global-groupings-q02', 'upsc-international-relations-major-global-groupings', 'The New Development Bank (NDB) of BRICS is headquartered in:', 'Moscow', 'New Delhi', 'Shanghai', 'Johannesburg', 'C', 'The BRICS New Development Bank is headquartered in Shanghai.', 1),
  ('upsc-international-relations-major-global-groupings-q03', 'upsc-international-relations-major-global-groupings', 'Consider the following statements:
1. SAARC was established in 1985 with its secretariat at Kathmandu.
2. ASEAN is central to India''s Act East policy.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'SAARC was set up in 1985 with its secretariat in Kathmandu; ASEAN anchors India''s Act East policy.', 2),
  ('upsc-international-relations-major-global-groupings-q04', 'upsc-international-relations-major-global-groupings', 'The I2U2 grouping comprises India, Israel, the USA and:', 'Saudi Arabia', 'Qatar', 'The United Arab Emirates', 'Egypt', 'C', 'I2U2 groups India, Israel, the United Arab Emirates and the United States.', 3),
  ('upsc-international-relations-major-global-groupings-q05', 'upsc-international-relations-major-global-groupings', 'India hosted the G20 summit in which year?', '2021', '2024', '2022', '2023', 'D', 'India hosted the G20 summit in 2023.', 4),
  ('upsc-international-relations-major-global-groupings-q06', 'upsc-international-relations-major-global-groupings', 'Consider the following statements:
1. India is a member of the MTCR.
2. India is a member of the Nuclear Suppliers Group (NSG).
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '1 only', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'B', 'India is a member of the MTCR but is not yet a member of the Nuclear Suppliers Group.', 5),
  ('upsc-international-relations-major-global-groupings-q07', 'upsc-international-relations-major-global-groupings', 'The grouping linking the countries around the Bay of Bengal is:', 'SAARC', 'BIMSTEC', 'ASEAN', 'SCO', 'B', 'BIMSTEC links South Asian and Southeast Asian nations around the Bay of Bengal.', 6),
  ('upsc-international-relations-major-global-groupings-q08', 'upsc-international-relations-major-global-groupings', 'Consider the following statements about India''s global standing:
1. India is a founding member of the United Nations (1945).
2. India is a permanent member of the UN Security Council.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'A', 'India is a founding UN member of 1945 but is not a permanent member of the Security Council.', 7),
  ('upsc-current-affairs-key-institutions-and-indices-q01', 'upsc-current-affairs-key-institutions-and-indices', 'The Human Development Index (HDI) is published by which organisation?', 'UNDP', 'IMF', 'WEF', 'World Bank', 'A', 'The HDI is published annually by the United Nations Development Programme (UNDP).', 0),
  ('upsc-current-affairs-key-institutions-and-indices-q02', 'upsc-current-affairs-key-institutions-and-indices', 'The Global Innovation Index is released by:', 'UNESCO', 'WTO', 'WIPO', 'WHO', 'C', 'The Global Innovation Index is released by the World Intellectual Property Organization (WIPO).', 1),
  ('upsc-current-affairs-key-institutions-and-indices-q03', 'upsc-current-affairs-key-institutions-and-indices', 'Consider the following statements:
1. NITI Aayog replaced the Planning Commission in 2015.
2. The HDI combines life expectancy, education and per capita income.
Which is/are correct?', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', '1 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'B', 'NITI Aayog replaced the Planning Commission in 2015; the HDI combines longevity, education and income.', 2),
  ('upsc-current-affairs-key-institutions-and-indices-q04', 'upsc-current-affairs-key-institutions-and-indices', 'The ''World Economic Outlook'' is published by which institution?', 'IMF', 'OECD', 'WEF', 'World Bank', 'A', 'The International Monetary Fund (IMF) publishes the World Economic Outlook.', 3),
  ('upsc-current-affairs-key-institutions-and-indices-q05', 'upsc-current-affairs-key-institutions-and-indices', 'The Global Gender Gap Report is released by the:', 'World Bank', 'World Economic Forum', 'UNDP', 'WHO', 'B', 'The World Economic Forum (WEF) releases the Global Gender Gap Report.', 4),
  ('upsc-current-affairs-key-institutions-and-indices-q06', 'upsc-current-affairs-key-institutions-and-indices', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Multidimensional Poverty Index is published jointly by UNDP and OPHI.
2. The Environmental Performance Index is released by Yale and Columbia universities.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'Both 1 and 2', 'D', 'The MPI is published by UNDP and OPHI; the EPI is released by Yale and Columbia universities.', 5),
  ('upsc-current-affairs-key-institutions-and-indices-q07', 'upsc-current-affairs-key-institutions-and-indices', 'The World Development Report is published by:', 'The IMF', 'The UNDP', 'The World Bank', 'The WTO', 'C', 'The World Bank publishes the World Development Report.', 6),
  ('upsc-current-affairs-key-institutions-and-indices-q08', 'upsc-current-affairs-key-institutions-and-indices', 'The World Happiness Report is published under the auspices of the:', 'WHO', 'Sustainable Development Solutions Network (SDSN)', 'World Bank', 'OECD', 'B', 'The World Happiness Report is released by the UN''s Sustainable Development Solutions Network (SDSN).', 7),
  ('upsc-current-affairs-polity-and-economy-in-the-news-q01', 'upsc-current-affairs-polity-and-economy-in-the-news', 'Anti-defection disqualifications are decided by whom under the Tenth Schedule?', 'The President', 'The Supreme Court', 'The Presiding Officer of the House', 'The Election Commission', 'C', 'Under the Tenth Schedule, the Presiding Officer of the House decides anti-defection disqualifications.', 0),
  ('upsc-current-affairs-polity-and-economy-in-the-news-q02', 'upsc-current-affairs-polity-and-economy-in-the-news', 'The Securities and Exchange Board of India (SEBI) was established in:', '1988', '1991', '1992', '2000', 'C', 'SEBI was given statutory status in 1992 to regulate securities markets and protect investors.', 1),
  ('upsc-current-affairs-polity-and-economy-in-the-news-q03', 'upsc-current-affairs-polity-and-economy-in-the-news', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The classification of a Money Bill is certified by the Speaker.
2. The Speaker''s decision on a Money Bill is final.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'The Speaker certifies a bill as a Money Bill under Article 110, and that decision is final.', 2),
  ('upsc-current-affairs-polity-and-economy-in-the-news-q04', 'upsc-current-affairs-polity-and-economy-in-the-news', 'A Governor''s options on a bill under Article 200 include assent, withholding assent and:', 'Dissolving the assembly', 'Reserving it for the President', 'Amending it directly', 'Issuing an ordinance', 'B', 'Under Article 200 a Governor may assent, withhold assent, or reserve a bill for the President''s consideration.', 3),
  ('upsc-current-affairs-polity-and-economy-in-the-news-q05', 'upsc-current-affairs-polity-and-economy-in-the-news', 'Disinvestment of public sector undertakings is managed by which body?', 'RBI', 'DIPAM', 'SEBI', 'NITI Aayog', 'B', 'Disinvestment is managed by DIPAM (Department of Investment and Public Asset Management).', 4),
  ('upsc-current-affairs-polity-and-economy-in-the-news-q06', 'upsc-current-affairs-polity-and-economy-in-the-news', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Election Commission conducts elections under Article 324.
2. The CAG audits and reports to Parliament under Article 148.
Which is/are correct?', 'Neither 1 nor 2', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', '1 only', 'C', 'The Election Commission acts under Article 324 and the CAG audits and reports under Article 148.', 5),
  ('upsc-current-affairs-polity-and-economy-in-the-news-q07', 'upsc-current-affairs-polity-and-economy-in-the-news', 'Inflation targeting in India is carried out by which body?', 'The Finance Commission', 'The GST Council', 'The Monetary Policy Committee of the RBI', 'SEBI', 'C', 'Inflation targeting is handled by the RBI''s Monetary Policy Committee (MPC).', 6),
  ('upsc-current-affairs-polity-and-economy-in-the-news-q08', 'upsc-current-affairs-polity-and-economy-in-the-news', 'Fiscal transfers between the Centre and the States are recommended by the:', 'Finance Commission', 'GST Council', 'NITI Aayog', 'RBI', 'A', 'The Finance Commission recommends fiscal transfers and tax devolution between the Centre and the States.', 7),
  ('upsc-polity-president-pm-and-council-of-ministers-q01', 'upsc-polity-president-pm-and-council-of-ministers', 'Under which Article is the President of India the head of the Union executive?', 'Article 74', 'Article 53', 'Article 52', 'Article 75', 'C', 'Article 52 provides that there shall be a President of India, the head of the Union executive.', 0),
  ('upsc-polity-president-pm-and-council-of-ministers-q02', 'upsc-polity-president-pm-and-council-of-ministers', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The President is elected by an electoral college through proportional representation.
2. The election uses the single transferable vote system.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', '1 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'A', 'Article 55 prescribes proportional representation by single transferable vote for the presidential election.', 1),
  ('upsc-polity-president-pm-and-council-of-ministers-q03', 'upsc-polity-president-pm-and-council-of-ministers', 'The total number of ministers in the Council cannot exceed what percentage of the Lok Sabha strength?', 'Ten per cent', 'Twelve per cent', 'Twenty per cent', 'Fifteen per cent', 'D', 'The 91st Amendment (2003) caps the Council of Ministers at 15 per cent of the Lok Sabha''s total strength.', 2),
  ('upsc-polity-president-pm-and-council-of-ministers-q04', 'upsc-polity-president-pm-and-council-of-ministers', 'The power of the President to grant pardons is contained in which Article?', 'Article 76', 'Article 72', 'Article 123', 'Article 61', 'B', 'Article 72 empowers the President to grant pardons, reprieves, respites and remissions of punishment.', 3),
  ('upsc-polity-president-pm-and-council-of-ministers-q05', 'upsc-polity-president-pm-and-council-of-ministers', 'The Council of Ministers is collectively responsible to which House?', 'The Rajya Sabha', 'The President', 'Both Houses jointly', 'The Lok Sabha', 'D', 'Article 75(3) makes the Council of Ministers collectively responsible to the Lok Sabha.', 4),
  ('upsc-polity-president-pm-and-council-of-ministers-q06', 'upsc-polity-president-pm-and-council-of-ministers', 'A person who is not a member of either House can remain a minister for a maximum of how long?', 'Three months', 'One year', 'Six months', 'Twelve months', 'C', 'Such a minister must become a member of either House within six months, failing which the post is vacated.', 5),
  ('upsc-polity-president-pm-and-council-of-ministers-q07', 'upsc-polity-president-pm-and-council-of-ministers', 'Under which Article does the President promulgate ordinances?', 'Article 123', 'Article 74', 'Article 72', 'Article 356', 'A', 'Article 123 empowers the President to promulgate ordinances when Parliament is not in session.', 6),
  ('upsc-polity-president-pm-and-council-of-ministers-q08', 'upsc-polity-president-pm-and-council-of-ministers', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The President normally acts on the aid and advice of the Council of Ministers.
2. The President may return such advice once for reconsideration.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'Both 1 and 2', 'D', 'Article 74, as amended by the 44th Amendment, lets the President return advice once but then must accept it.', 7),
  ('upsc-polity-federalism-and-centre-state-relations-q01', 'upsc-polity-federalism-and-centre-state-relations', 'The division of legislative powers between the Centre and States is contained in which Schedule?', 'Seventh Schedule', 'Sixth Schedule', 'Fifth Schedule', 'Tenth Schedule', 'A', 'The Seventh Schedule contains the Union, State and Concurrent Lists distributing legislative powers.', 0),
  ('upsc-polity-federalism-and-centre-state-relations-q02', 'upsc-polity-federalism-and-centre-state-relations', 'In whom do the residuary powers of legislation vest?', 'The State Legislatures', 'The Union Parliament', 'The President', 'The Inter-State Council', 'B', 'Article 248 vests residuary powers of legislation in the Union Parliament.', 1),
  ('upsc-polity-federalism-and-centre-state-relations-q03', 'upsc-polity-federalism-and-centre-state-relations', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Police and public order are subjects in the State List.
2. Education is a subject in the Concurrent List.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', '1 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'A', 'Police and public order fall in the State List, while education is on the Concurrent List after the 42nd Amendment.', 2),
  ('upsc-polity-federalism-and-centre-state-relations-q04', 'upsc-polity-federalism-and-centre-state-relations', 'Which commission was set up in 1983 to examine Centre-State relations?', 'The Punchhi Commission', 'The Rajamannar Committee', 'The Sarkaria Commission', 'The Mandal Commission', 'C', 'The Sarkaria Commission (1983) was appointed to review Centre-State relations; the Punchhi Commission came in 2007.', 3),
  ('upsc-polity-federalism-and-centre-state-relations-q05', 'upsc-polity-federalism-and-centre-state-relations', 'Parliament can legislate on a State subject in the national interest if the Rajya Sabha passes a resolution under which Article?', 'Article 280', 'Article 256', 'Article 262', 'Article 249', 'D', 'Article 249 lets Parliament legislate on a State subject if the Rajya Sabha resolves so in the national interest.', 4),
  ('upsc-polity-federalism-and-centre-state-relations-q06', 'upsc-polity-federalism-and-centre-state-relations', 'Which body is described by some scholars as an example of cooperative federalism in India?', 'The Supreme Court', 'The Election Commission', 'The GST Council', 'The Comptroller and Auditor General', 'C', 'The GST Council, with Centre and States deciding tax rates jointly, exemplifies cooperative federalism.', 5),
  ('upsc-polity-federalism-and-centre-state-relations-q07', 'upsc-polity-federalism-and-centre-state-relations', 'The Inter-State Council can be established by the President under which Article?', 'Article 131', 'Article 324', 'Article 280', 'Article 263', 'D', 'Article 263 empowers the President to establish an Inter-State Council to coordinate between states and the Centre.', 6),
  ('upsc-polity-federalism-and-centre-state-relations-q08', 'upsc-polity-federalism-and-centre-state-relations', 'When a Union law and a State law on a Concurrent subject conflict, which prevails?', 'The State law', 'Neither, both are void', 'The earlier law', 'The Union law', 'D', 'Under Article 254, the Union law generally prevails over a conflicting State law on a Concurrent List subject.', 7),
  ('upsc-polity-panchayati-raj-and-local-government-q01', 'upsc-polity-panchayati-raj-and-local-government', 'Which Constitutional Amendment gave panchayats constitutional status?', '74th Amendment', '73rd Amendment', '65th Amendment', '44th Amendment', 'B', 'The 73rd Amendment (1992) added Part IX, giving panchayati raj institutions constitutional status.', 0),
  ('upsc-polity-panchayati-raj-and-local-government-q02', 'upsc-polity-panchayati-raj-and-local-government', 'The three-tier system of panchayati raj is mandatory for states with a population above:', 'Ten lakh', 'Twenty lakh', 'Fifteen lakh', 'Fifty lakh', 'B', 'States with a population above twenty lakh must constitute the three-tier panchayati raj system.', 1),
  ('upsc-polity-panchayati-raj-and-local-government-q03', 'upsc-polity-panchayati-raj-and-local-government', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Eleventh Schedule lists subjects for panchayats.
2. The Twelfth Schedule lists subjects for municipalities.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'Both 1 and 2', 'D', 'The Eleventh Schedule has 29 subjects for panchayats; the Twelfth Schedule has 18 for municipalities.', 2),
  ('upsc-polity-panchayati-raj-and-local-government-q04', 'upsc-polity-panchayati-raj-and-local-government', 'Which committee first recommended the three-tier panchayati raj system?', 'The Balwant Rai Mehta Committee', 'The Ashok Mehta Committee', 'The L.M. Singhvi Committee', 'The G.V.K. Rao Committee', 'A', 'The Balwant Rai Mehta Committee (1957) recommended the three-tier structure of panchayati raj.', 3),
  ('upsc-polity-panchayati-raj-and-local-government-q05', 'upsc-polity-panchayati-raj-and-local-government', 'The conduct of elections to panchayats is vested in the:', 'Election Commission of India', 'District Collector', 'State Finance Commission', 'State Election Commission', 'D', 'Article 243K vests superintendence of panchayat elections in the State Election Commission.', 4),
  ('upsc-polity-panchayati-raj-and-local-government-q06', 'upsc-polity-panchayati-raj-and-local-government', 'What is the fixed term of a panchayat under Article 243E?', 'Four years', 'Six years', 'Five years', 'Three years', 'C', 'Article 243E fixes a five-year term for every panchayat from the date of its first meeting.', 5),
  ('upsc-polity-panchayati-raj-and-local-government-q07', 'upsc-polity-panchayati-raj-and-local-government', 'The PESA Act, 1996 extends panchayat provisions to which areas?', 'Urban municipal areas', 'Sixth Schedule areas', 'Union Territories', 'Fifth Schedule (tribal) areas', 'D', 'The PESA Act, 1996 extends Part IX provisions to the Scheduled (Fifth Schedule) tribal areas.', 6),
  ('upsc-polity-panchayati-raj-and-local-government-q08', 'upsc-polity-panchayati-raj-and-local-government', 'The financial position of panchayats is reviewed every five years by the:', 'Union Finance Commission', 'NITI Aayog', 'Comptroller and Auditor General', 'State Finance Commission', 'D', 'Article 243I provides for a State Finance Commission to review panchayat finances every five years.', 7),
  ('upsc-polity-emergency-provisions-and-amendments-q01', 'upsc-polity-emergency-provisions-and-amendments', 'A National Emergency is proclaimed under which Article?', 'Article 368', 'Article 356', 'Article 360', 'Article 352', 'D', 'Article 352 allows a National Emergency on grounds of war, external aggression or armed rebellion.', 0),
  ('upsc-polity-emergency-provisions-and-amendments-q02', 'upsc-polity-emergency-provisions-and-amendments', 'President''s Rule in a State is imposed under which Article?', 'Article 352', 'Article 360', 'Article 356', 'Article 365', 'C', 'Article 356 provides for President''s Rule when the constitutional machinery in a State fails.', 1),
  ('upsc-polity-emergency-provisions-and-amendments-q03', 'upsc-polity-emergency-provisions-and-amendments', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The 44th Amendment replaced ''internal disturbance'' with ''armed rebellion''.
2. A National Emergency must be approved by Parliament within one month.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', '1 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'A', 'The 44th Amendment substituted ''armed rebellion'' and required parliamentary approval within one month.', 2),
  ('upsc-polity-emergency-provisions-and-amendments-q04', 'upsc-polity-emergency-provisions-and-amendments', 'Which case made the imposition of President''s Rule subject to judicial review?', 'S.R. Bommai case', 'Minerva Mills case', 'Kesavananda Bharati case', 'Maneka Gandhi case', 'A', 'The S.R. Bommai (1994) case held that President''s Rule under Article 356 is subject to judicial review.', 3),
  ('upsc-polity-emergency-provisions-and-amendments-q05', 'upsc-polity-emergency-provisions-and-amendments', 'The procedure for amending the Constitution is laid down in which Article?', 'Article 360', 'Article 352', 'Article 370', 'Article 368', 'D', 'Article 368 lays down the procedure for amending the Constitution.', 4),
  ('upsc-polity-emergency-provisions-and-amendments-q06', 'upsc-polity-emergency-provisions-and-amendments', 'Which amendment is popularly called the ''Mini-Constitution''?', '73rd Amendment', '44th Amendment', '1st Amendment', '42nd Amendment', 'D', 'The 42nd Amendment (1976) made sweeping changes and is known as the ''Mini-Constitution''.', 5),
  ('upsc-polity-emergency-provisions-and-amendments-q07', 'upsc-polity-emergency-provisions-and-amendments', 'The doctrine that Parliament cannot alter the ''basic structure'' was laid down in which case?', 'Kesavananda Bharati case', 'Golaknath case', 'Shankari Prasad case', 'Indira Sawhney case', 'A', 'The Kesavananda Bharati (1973) case established the basic structure doctrine limiting Article 368.', 6),
  ('upsc-polity-emergency-provisions-and-amendments-q08', 'upsc-polity-emergency-provisions-and-amendments', 'A Financial Emergency can be proclaimed under which Article?', 'Article 352', 'Article 356', 'Article 360', 'Article 365', 'C', 'Article 360 provides for a Financial Emergency on a threat to the financial stability or credit of India.', 7),
  ('upsc-economy-taxation-and-gst-q01', 'upsc-economy-taxation-and-gst', 'GST in India was introduced by which Constitutional Amendment?', '103rd Amendment', '100th Amendment', '102nd Amendment', '101st Amendment', 'D', 'The 101st Amendment Act, 2016 introduced the Goods and Services Tax, effective from 1 July 2017.', 0),
  ('upsc-economy-taxation-and-gst-q02', 'upsc-economy-taxation-and-gst', 'The GST Council is established under which Article?', 'Article 246A', 'Article 280', 'Article 279A', 'Article 110', 'C', 'Article 279A provides for the constitution of the GST Council, chaired by the Union Finance Minister.', 1),
  ('upsc-economy-taxation-and-gst-q03', 'upsc-economy-taxation-and-gst', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Income tax is a direct tax.
2. GST is an indirect tax.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'Income tax is a direct tax borne by the payer, while GST is an indirect tax that can be passed on.', 2),
  ('upsc-economy-taxation-and-gst-q04', 'upsc-economy-taxation-and-gst', 'GST levied on inter-state supply of goods is known as:', 'IGST', 'SGST', 'CGST', 'UTGST', 'A', 'Integrated GST (IGST) is levied by the Centre on inter-state supplies of goods and services.', 3),
  ('upsc-economy-taxation-and-gst-q05', 'upsc-economy-taxation-and-gst', 'Which of the following is currently outside the ambit of GST?', 'Restaurant services', 'Electronics', 'Textiles', 'Petroleum products', 'D', 'Petroleum products, alcohol for human consumption and electricity remain outside GST at present.', 4),
  ('upsc-economy-taxation-and-gst-q06', 'upsc-economy-taxation-and-gst', 'GST is best described as which kind of tax?', 'Origin-based tax', 'A wealth tax', 'A direct tax', 'Destination-based tax', 'D', 'GST is a destination-based, value-added tax collected at the point of consumption.', 5),
  ('upsc-economy-taxation-and-gst-q07', 'upsc-economy-taxation-and-gst', 'The Laffer Curve illustrates the relationship between:', 'Inflation and unemployment', 'Tax rates and tax revenue', 'Savings and investment', 'Demand and supply', 'B', 'The Laffer Curve shows that beyond a point, higher tax rates can reduce total tax revenue.', 6),
  ('upsc-economy-taxation-and-gst-q08', 'upsc-economy-taxation-and-gst', 'Tax buoyancy refers to the responsiveness of tax revenue to changes in:', 'GDP / national income', 'The repo rate', 'The exchange rate', 'The fiscal deficit', 'A', 'Tax buoyancy measures how tax revenue responds to growth in GDP or national income.', 7),
  ('upsc-economy-poverty-unemployment-and-inclusive-growth-q01', 'upsc-economy-poverty-unemployment-and-inclusive-growth', 'Which type of unemployment is most associated with Indian agriculture?', 'Frictional unemployment', 'Cyclical unemployment', 'Voluntary unemployment', 'Disguised unemployment', 'D', 'Disguised unemployment, where surplus workers add little output, is common in Indian agriculture.', 0),
  ('upsc-economy-poverty-unemployment-and-inclusive-growth-q02', 'upsc-economy-poverty-unemployment-and-inclusive-growth', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Tendulkar Committee estimated poverty based on consumption expenditure.
2. The Rangarajan Committee later reviewed poverty estimation.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'B', 'Both the Tendulkar (2009) and Rangarajan (2014) committees estimated poverty using consumption expenditure.', 1),
  ('upsc-economy-poverty-unemployment-and-inclusive-growth-q03', 'upsc-economy-poverty-unemployment-and-inclusive-growth', 'The Gini coefficient is a measure of:', 'Inflation', 'Economic growth', 'Income inequality', 'Tax efficiency', 'C', 'The Gini coefficient measures income inequality, ranging from 0 (perfect equality) to 1 (perfect inequality).', 2),
  ('upsc-economy-poverty-unemployment-and-inclusive-growth-q04', 'upsc-economy-poverty-unemployment-and-inclusive-growth', 'Which survey is the primary official source of employment data in India?', 'National Family Health Survey', 'National Sample Survey on Consumption', 'Census of India', 'Periodic Labour Force Survey', 'D', 'The Periodic Labour Force Survey (PLFS) by the NSO is the main source of employment and unemployment data.', 3),
  ('upsc-economy-poverty-unemployment-and-inclusive-growth-q05', 'upsc-economy-poverty-unemployment-and-inclusive-growth', 'Unemployment arising from a mismatch between workers'' skills and job requirements is called:', 'Structural unemployment', 'Cyclical unemployment', 'Frictional unemployment', 'Seasonal unemployment', 'A', 'Structural unemployment results from a mismatch between available skills and the demands of the economy.', 4),
  ('upsc-economy-poverty-unemployment-and-inclusive-growth-q06', 'upsc-economy-poverty-unemployment-and-inclusive-growth', 'The Multidimensional Poverty Index in India is released by:', 'The RBI', 'NITI Aayog', 'SEBI', 'The Finance Commission', 'B', 'NITI Aayog releases the national Multidimensional Poverty Index covering health, education and living standards.', 5),
  ('upsc-economy-poverty-unemployment-and-inclusive-growth-q07', 'upsc-economy-poverty-unemployment-and-inclusive-growth', 'The Lorenz Curve is used to depict:', 'The business cycle', 'Marginal utility', 'The distribution of income', 'Price elasticity', 'C', 'The Lorenz Curve graphically represents the distribution of income or wealth in an economy.', 6),
  ('upsc-economy-poverty-unemployment-and-inclusive-growth-q08', 'upsc-economy-poverty-unemployment-and-inclusive-growth', 'Which programme guarantees 100 days of wage employment to rural households?', 'PM-KISAN', 'PM Awas Yojana', 'PMKVY', 'MGNREGA', 'D', 'MGNREGA guarantees 100 days of wage employment per year to every rural household demanding work.', 7),
  ('upsc-economy-external-sector-and-trade-q01', 'upsc-economy-external-sector-and-trade', 'The current account of the Balance of Payments includes:', 'Trade in goods, services and remittances', 'Foreign direct investment', 'External commercial borrowings', 'Portfolio investment', 'A', 'The current account records trade in goods and services, income and current transfers like remittances.', 0),
  ('upsc-economy-external-sector-and-trade-q02', 'upsc-economy-external-sector-and-trade', 'Consider the following statements:
1. FDI is generally long-term and involves management control.
2. FPI is short-term portfolio investment often called ''hot money''.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'FDI is durable and management-linked, while FPI is volatile portfolio flow termed ''hot money''.', 1),
  ('upsc-economy-external-sector-and-trade-q03', 'upsc-economy-external-sector-and-trade', 'Depreciation of the rupee generally makes:', 'Exports costlier and imports cheaper', 'No change in trade flows', 'Both exports and imports cheaper', 'Exports cheaper and imports costlier', 'D', 'A weaker rupee makes Indian exports cheaper abroad and imports more expensive at home.', 2),
  ('upsc-economy-external-sector-and-trade-q04', 'upsc-economy-external-sector-and-trade', 'India''s exchange rate system is best described as:', 'Fixed peg', 'Free float', 'Managed float', 'Currency board', 'C', 'India follows a managed floating exchange rate, with the RBI intervening to limit volatility.', 3),
  ('upsc-economy-external-sector-and-trade-q05', 'upsc-economy-external-sector-and-trade', 'A Current Account Deficit arises when:', 'Exports exceed imports of goods and services', 'Forex reserves rise', 'Capital inflows exceed outflows', 'Imports of goods and services exceed exports plus net transfers', 'D', 'A CAD occurs when a country''s imports of goods and services exceed exports and net current transfers.', 4),
  ('upsc-economy-external-sector-and-trade-q06', 'upsc-economy-external-sector-and-trade', 'Which body administers India''s Foreign Trade Policy?', 'The RBI', 'The Directorate General of Foreign Trade', 'SEBI', 'The Finance Commission', 'B', 'The Directorate General of Foreign Trade (DGFT) administers India''s Foreign Trade Policy.', 5),
  ('upsc-economy-external-sector-and-trade-q07', 'upsc-economy-external-sector-and-trade', 'Which of the following is classified as an ''invisible'' in the Balance of Payments?', 'Software services and remittances', 'Import of crude oil', 'Export of machinery', 'Import of gold', 'A', 'Services and remittances are ''invisibles'', as against visible merchandise trade in goods.', 6),
  ('upsc-economy-external-sector-and-trade-q08', 'upsc-economy-external-sector-and-trade', 'The global body that frames the rules of international trade is the:', 'IMF', 'WTO', 'World Bank', 'UNCTAD', 'B', 'The World Trade Organization (WTO), established in 1995, frames and enforces global trade rules.', 7),
  ('upsc-economy-agriculture-and-food-security-q01', 'upsc-economy-agriculture-and-food-security', 'The Minimum Support Price (MSP) is recommended by which body?', 'The Food Corporation of India', 'The Commission for Agricultural Costs and Prices', 'NABARD', 'The NITI Aayog', 'B', 'The Commission for Agricultural Costs and Prices (CACP) recommends the MSP to the government.', 0),
  ('upsc-economy-agriculture-and-food-security-q02', 'upsc-economy-agriculture-and-food-security', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The National Food Security Act was enacted in 2013.
2. It gives a legal right to subsidised foodgrains.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'Both 1 and 2', 'D', 'The National Food Security Act, 2013 gives a legal entitlement to subsidised foodgrains via the PDS.', 1),
  ('upsc-economy-agriculture-and-food-security-q03', 'upsc-economy-agriculture-and-food-security', 'Procurement of foodgrains for the central pool is handled mainly by the:', 'Food Corporation of India', 'NABARD', 'RBI', 'CACP', 'A', 'The Food Corporation of India (FCI) is the principal agency for procurement and buffer stocking.', 2),
  ('upsc-economy-agriculture-and-food-security-q04', 'upsc-economy-agriculture-and-food-security', 'The apex institution for agricultural and rural credit in India is:', 'NABARD', 'SIDBI', 'The RBI', 'EXIM Bank', 'A', 'NABARD is the apex development bank for agriculture and rural credit in India.', 3),
  ('upsc-economy-agriculture-and-food-security-q05', 'upsc-economy-agriculture-and-food-security', 'The ''One Nation One Ration Card'' scheme primarily enables:', 'Crop insurance', 'Portability of PDS benefits across states', 'Free electricity to farmers', 'Direct cash transfer of MSP', 'B', 'One Nation One Ration Card allows beneficiaries to access PDS rations anywhere in the country.', 4),
  ('upsc-economy-agriculture-and-food-security-q06', 'upsc-economy-agriculture-and-food-security', 'MSP has been declared as a benchmark of how many times the A2+FL cost?', '1.2 times', '1 time', '2 times', '1.5 times', 'D', 'The government announced MSP at a level of at least 1.5 times the A2+FL cost of production.', 5),
  ('upsc-economy-agriculture-and-food-security-q07', 'upsc-economy-agriculture-and-food-security', 'e-NAM is best described as:', 'A unified national online agricultural market', 'A crop insurance scheme', 'A fertiliser subsidy portal', 'A soil health card scheme', 'A', 'e-NAM is the electronic National Agriculture Market, a unified online trading platform for farm produce.', 6),
  ('upsc-economy-agriculture-and-food-security-q08', 'upsc-economy-agriculture-and-food-security', 'The Green Revolution in India is most associated with which crops?', 'Pulses and oilseeds', 'Cotton and jute', 'Wheat and rice', 'Tea and coffee', 'C', 'The Green Revolution sharply raised the output of wheat and rice through high-yielding varieties.', 7),
  ('upsc-international-relations-important-international-organizations-q01', 'upsc-international-relations-important-international-organizations', 'How many permanent members does the UN Security Council have?', 'Seven', 'Ten', 'Fifteen', 'Five', 'D', 'The UNSC has five permanent members (USA, UK, France, Russia, China) with veto power.', 0),
  ('upsc-international-relations-important-international-organizations-q02', 'upsc-international-relations-important-international-organizations', 'Where is the International Court of Justice located?', 'New York', 'The Hague', 'Geneva', 'Vienna', 'B', 'The International Court of Justice, the principal judicial organ of the UN, sits at The Hague.', 1),
  ('upsc-international-relations-important-international-organizations-q03', 'upsc-international-relations-important-international-organizations', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The IMF and the World Bank are Bretton Woods institutions.
2. Both are headquartered in Washington DC.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'B', 'The IMF and World Bank emerged from the 1944 Bretton Woods Conference and are based in Washington DC.', 2),
  ('upsc-international-relations-important-international-organizations-q04', 'upsc-international-relations-important-international-organizations', 'Special Drawing Rights (SDRs) are issued by which institution?', 'The World Bank', 'The WTO', 'The IMF', 'The Asian Development Bank', 'C', 'Special Drawing Rights are an international reserve asset created and allocated by the IMF.', 3),
  ('upsc-international-relations-important-international-organizations-q05', 'upsc-international-relations-important-international-organizations', 'The International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) is headquartered in:', 'Geneva', 'Vienna', 'Paris', 'New York', 'B', 'The IAEA, which promotes peaceful use of nuclear energy, is headquartered in Vienna.', 4),
  ('upsc-international-relations-important-international-organizations-q06', 'upsc-international-relations-important-international-organizations', 'Which is the only tripartite agency of the United Nations?', 'The WHO', 'The ILO', 'UNESCO', 'UNICEF', 'B', 'The International Labour Organization (ILO) is unique in bringing together governments, employers and workers.', 5),
  ('upsc-international-relations-important-international-organizations-q07', 'upsc-international-relations-important-international-organizations', 'The WTO, governing global trade rules, came into existence in which year?', '1945', '1995', '1948', '2001', 'B', 'The World Trade Organization was established in 1995, succeeding the GATT.', 6),
  ('upsc-international-relations-important-international-organizations-q08', 'upsc-international-relations-important-international-organizations', 'The G4 group, which seeks permanent UNSC seats, consists of India, Germany, Japan and:', 'Australia', 'South Africa', 'Italy', 'Brazil', 'D', 'The G4 nations seeking permanent UN Security Council seats are India, Germany, Japan and Brazil.', 7),
  ('upsc-international-relations-indias-foreign-policy-and-diaspora-q01', 'upsc-international-relations-indias-foreign-policy-and-diaspora', 'The Panchsheel principles were enunciated in which year?', '1947', '1950', '1962', '1954', 'D', 'The Panchsheel, the Five Principles of Peaceful Coexistence, were articulated in 1954.', 0),
  ('upsc-international-relations-indias-foreign-policy-and-diaspora-q02', 'upsc-international-relations-indias-foreign-policy-and-diaspora', 'SAGAR, a maritime vision, stands for:', 'Security and Growth for All in the Region', 'Strategic Action for Global Asian Regions', 'South Asian Group for African Relations', 'Safe Anchorage and Gulf Access Route', 'A', 'SAGAR stands for ''Security and Growth for All in the Region'', India''s maritime cooperation vision.', 1),
  ('upsc-international-relations-indias-foreign-policy-and-diaspora-q03', 'upsc-international-relations-indias-foreign-policy-and-diaspora', 'Consider the following statements:
1. India has the largest overseas diaspora in the world.
2. India is among the top recipients of remittances.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'India has the world''s largest diaspora and is the leading recipient of remittances globally.', 2),
  ('upsc-international-relations-indias-foreign-policy-and-diaspora-q04', 'upsc-international-relations-indias-foreign-policy-and-diaspora', 'Pravasi Bharatiya Divas is observed on which date?', '9 January', '26 January', '15 August', '2 October', 'A', 'Pravasi Bharatiya Divas is observed on 9 January, marking Gandhi''s return from South Africa in 1915.', 3),
  ('upsc-international-relations-indias-foreign-policy-and-diaspora-q05', 'upsc-international-relations-indias-foreign-policy-and-diaspora', 'India''s ''Act East'' policy is chiefly directed toward:', 'ASEAN and East Asia', 'Africa', 'The Gulf countries', 'Latin America', 'A', 'The Act East policy strengthens India''s economic and strategic ties with ASEAN and East Asia.', 4),
  ('upsc-international-relations-indias-foreign-policy-and-diaspora-q06', 'upsc-international-relations-indias-foreign-policy-and-diaspora', 'Which leader is most closely associated with shaping the Non-Aligned Movement for India?', 'Sardar Patel', 'Lal Bahadur Shastri', 'Jawaharlal Nehru', 'B.R. Ambedkar', 'C', 'Jawaharlal Nehru was a principal architect of India''s non-alignment and the Non-Aligned Movement.', 5),
  ('upsc-international-relations-indias-foreign-policy-and-diaspora-q07', 'upsc-international-relations-indias-foreign-policy-and-diaspora', 'An Overseas Citizen of India (OCI) cardholder is generally:', 'A foreign citizen of Indian origin with visa-free entry', 'An Indian citizen by birth', 'Allowed to vote in Indian elections', 'Eligible to hold constitutional office', 'A', 'An OCI is a foreign citizen of Indian origin given lifelong visa-free entry but no voting rights.', 6),
  ('upsc-international-relations-indias-foreign-policy-and-diaspora-q08', 'upsc-international-relations-indias-foreign-policy-and-diaspora', 'Indian diplomacy and foreign relations are primarily conducted by which ministry?', 'Ministry of Home Affairs', 'Ministry of External Affairs', 'Ministry of Defence', 'Ministry of Commerce', 'B', 'The Ministry of External Affairs (MEA) conducts India''s diplomacy and foreign relations.', 7),
  ('upsc-ethics-ethics-and-human-interface-q01', 'upsc-ethics-ethics-and-human-interface', 'Ethics is best defined as:', 'A set of legal rules', 'The systematic study of morality', 'Individual personal preferences', 'Religious commandments only', 'B', 'Ethics is the systematic, reflective study of morality and standards of right and wrong conduct.', 0),
  ('upsc-ethics-ethics-and-human-interface-q02', 'upsc-ethics-ethics-and-human-interface', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Deontology judges an act by its consequences.
2. Consequentialism judges an act by its outcomes.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'B', 'Deontology judges acts by adherence to duty, while consequentialism judges them by their outcomes.', 1),
  ('upsc-ethics-ethics-and-human-interface-q03', 'upsc-ethics-ethics-and-human-interface', 'The branch of ethics that analyses the meaning of moral terms is called:', 'Meta-ethics', 'Normative ethics', 'Descriptive ethics', 'Applied ethics', 'A', 'Meta-ethics examines the nature and meaning of moral concepts such as ''good'' and ''right''.', 2),
  ('upsc-ethics-ethics-and-human-interface-q04', 'upsc-ethics-ethics-and-human-interface', 'Which is often described as the inner moral guide or ''court of last appeal''?', 'Law', 'Conscience', 'Custom', 'Public opinion', 'B', 'Conscience is regarded as the inner moral compass, the final internal arbiter of right and wrong.', 3),
  ('upsc-ethics-ethics-and-human-interface-q05', 'upsc-ethics-ethics-and-human-interface', 'Morals differ from ethics in that morals are:', 'The systematic study of conduct', 'Identical to legal rules', 'Always codified in law', 'Personal beliefs of right and wrong', 'D', 'Morals are an individual''s personal convictions, whereas ethics is the reasoned study of those convictions.', 4),
  ('upsc-ethics-ethics-and-human-interface-q06', 'upsc-ethics-ethics-and-human-interface', 'Normative ethics is primarily concerned with:', 'What people ought to do', 'What people actually do', 'The meaning of moral language', 'Statistical study of behaviour', 'A', 'Normative ethics prescribes the standards of how people ought to act.', 5),
  ('upsc-ethics-ethics-and-human-interface-q07', 'upsc-ethics-ethics-and-human-interface', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Public conduct demands higher accountability than private conduct.
2. Conscience is regarded as a source of ethics.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', '1 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'A', 'Public actions affect many and demand higher accountability, and conscience is a recognised source of ethics.', 6),
  ('upsc-ethics-ethics-and-human-interface-q08', 'upsc-ethics-ethics-and-human-interface', 'Which of the following is NOT generally considered a source of ethics?', 'Religion', 'Random chance', 'The Constitution', 'Society and family', 'B', 'Family, religion, society and the constitution shape ethics; random chance is not a source of moral values.', 7),
  ('upsc-ethics-attitude-and-emotional-intelligence-q01', 'upsc-ethics-attitude-and-emotional-intelligence', 'The three components of attitude in the ABC model are affective, behavioural and:', 'Contextual', 'Compulsive', 'Cognitive', 'Cultural', 'C', 'The ABC model of attitude comprises affective (feelings), behavioural and cognitive (beliefs) components.', 0),
  ('upsc-ethics-attitude-and-emotional-intelligence-q02', 'upsc-ethics-attitude-and-emotional-intelligence', 'The concept of Emotional Intelligence was popularised by:', 'Abraham Maslow', 'Sigmund Freud', 'Daniel Goleman', 'Leon Festinger', 'C', 'Daniel Goleman popularised Emotional Intelligence through his widely read work on the subject.', 1),
  ('upsc-ethics-attitude-and-emotional-intelligence-q03', 'upsc-ethics-attitude-and-emotional-intelligence', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Prejudice is a negative attitude toward a group.
2. Discrimination is the behavioural expression of prejudice.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'Both 1 and 2', 'D', 'Prejudice is a negative attitude, and discrimination is its behavioural manifestation.', 2),
  ('upsc-ethics-attitude-and-emotional-intelligence-q04', 'upsc-ethics-attitude-and-emotional-intelligence', 'Which is NOT one of Goleman''s five elements of Emotional Intelligence?', 'Intelligence quotient', 'Empathy', 'Self-awareness', 'Self-regulation', 'A', 'Goleman''s elements are self-awareness, self-regulation, motivation, empathy and social skills; IQ is separate.', 3),
  ('upsc-ethics-attitude-and-emotional-intelligence-q05', 'upsc-ethics-attitude-and-emotional-intelligence', 'The mental discomfort from holding conflicting beliefs is termed:', 'Cognitive bias', 'Cognitive dissonance', 'Cognitive load', 'Cognitive map', 'B', 'Leon Festinger''s cognitive dissonance describes discomfort from holding inconsistent beliefs or attitudes.', 4),
  ('upsc-ethics-attitude-and-emotional-intelligence-q06', 'upsc-ethics-attitude-and-emotional-intelligence', 'A stereotype is best described as the ___ component of an attitude toward a group.', 'Affective', 'Behavioural', 'Cognitive', 'Physiological', 'C', 'A stereotype is the cognitive component, a generalised belief about members of a group.', 5),
  ('upsc-ethics-attitude-and-emotional-intelligence-q07', 'upsc-ethics-attitude-and-emotional-intelligence', 'Which feature best characterises attitudes?', 'They are innate and fixed at birth', 'They change every moment', 'They cannot influence behaviour', 'They are learned and relatively enduring', 'D', 'Attitudes are learned, relatively enduring evaluations that influence behaviour.', 6),
  ('upsc-ethics-attitude-and-emotional-intelligence-q08', 'upsc-ethics-attitude-and-emotional-intelligence', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Empathy is a component of emotional intelligence.
2. High emotional intelligence helps an administrator manage stress.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'Empathy is central to EI, and high EI aids stress management and balanced decision-making.', 7),
  ('upsc-ethics-moral-thinkers-and-philosophers-q01', 'upsc-ethics-moral-thinkers-and-philosophers', 'The ''categorical imperative'' is a core idea of which philosopher?', 'Aristotle', 'Jeremy Bentham', 'Immanuel Kant', 'John Rawls', 'C', 'Immanuel Kant''s categorical imperative requires acting only on maxims that could be universal laws.', 0),
  ('upsc-ethics-moral-thinkers-and-philosophers-q02', 'upsc-ethics-moral-thinkers-and-philosophers', 'The principle of the ''greatest happiness of the greatest number'' is associated with:', 'Deontology', 'Virtue ethics', 'Existentialism', 'Utilitarianism', 'D', 'Utilitarianism, advanced by Bentham and Mill, seeks the greatest happiness of the greatest number.', 1),
  ('upsc-ethics-moral-thinkers-and-philosophers-q03', 'upsc-ethics-moral-thinkers-and-philosophers', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Aristotle is associated with virtue ethics and the golden mean.
2. John Rawls proposed the ''veil of ignorance''.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'Aristotle gave virtue ethics and the golden mean; Rawls proposed the veil of ignorance for justice.', 2),
  ('upsc-ethics-moral-thinkers-and-philosophers-q04', 'upsc-ethics-moral-thinkers-and-philosophers', 'Gandhi''s idea that the wealthy hold their riches in trust for society is called:', 'Satyagraha', 'Sarvodaya', 'Trusteeship', 'Swadeshi', 'C', 'Gandhi''s trusteeship doctrine holds that the rich should manage wealth for the welfare of society.', 3),
  ('upsc-ethics-moral-thinkers-and-philosophers-q05', 'upsc-ethics-moral-thinkers-and-philosophers', 'According to Aristotle, virtue lies in:', 'The greatest pleasure', 'Maximising utility', 'Strict obedience to law', 'The golden mean between extremes', 'D', 'Aristotle held that moral virtue is the golden mean between two vices of excess and deficiency.', 4),
  ('upsc-ethics-moral-thinkers-and-philosophers-q06', 'upsc-ethics-moral-thinkers-and-philosophers', 'The concept of ''Nishkama Karma'', action without attachment to results, is taught in the:', 'Bhagavad Gita', 'Arthashastra', 'Republic', 'Leviathan', 'A', 'The Bhagavad Gita teaches Nishkama Karma, performing one''s duty without attachment to its fruits.', 5),
  ('upsc-ethics-moral-thinkers-and-philosophers-q07', 'upsc-ethics-moral-thinkers-and-philosophers', 'Which thinker linked ethics with statecraft in the Arthashastra?', 'Confucius', 'Plato', 'Kautilya', 'Socrates', 'C', 'Kautilya (Chanakya) integrated ethics with practical statecraft and economy in the Arthashastra.', 6),
  ('upsc-ethics-moral-thinkers-and-philosophers-q08', 'upsc-ethics-moral-thinkers-and-philosophers', 'Swami Vivekananda chiefly emphasised:', 'Renunciation of all action', 'Pursuit of personal wealth', 'Service to humanity as worship', 'Absolute obedience to authority', 'C', 'Vivekananda taught that selfless service to humanity is a form of worship of the divine.', 7),
  ('upsc-ethics-public-civil-service-values-q01', 'upsc-ethics-public-civil-service-values', 'The ''Seven Principles of Public Life'' were articulated by which committee?', 'The Nolan Committee', 'The Santhanam Committee', 'The Hota Committee', 'The Sarkaria Commission', 'A', 'The UK''s Nolan Committee laid down the Seven Principles of Public Life.', 0),
  ('upsc-ethics-public-civil-service-values-q02', 'upsc-ethics-public-civil-service-values', 'Which value requires a civil servant to treat all citizens without favour or bias?', 'Anonymity', 'Impartiality', 'Secrecy', 'Hierarchy', 'B', 'Impartiality requires treating all citizens equally, without favour, bias or discrimination.', 1),
  ('upsc-ethics-public-civil-service-values-q03', 'upsc-ethics-public-civil-service-values', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Integrity means honesty and wholeness in conduct.
2. Objectivity means deciding on merit and evidence.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'Both 1 and 2', 'D', 'Integrity is honesty and consistency, while objectivity means basing decisions on merit and evidence.', 2),
  ('upsc-ethics-public-civil-service-values-q04', 'upsc-ethics-public-civil-service-values', 'Conduct of All India Service officers is governed by which rules?', 'Representation of the People Act, 1951', 'All India Services (Conduct) Rules, 1968', 'Right to Information Act, 2005', 'Indian Penal Code, 1860', 'B', 'The All India Services (Conduct) Rules, 1968 govern the conduct of All India Service officers.', 3),
  ('upsc-ethics-public-civil-service-values-q05', 'upsc-ethics-public-civil-service-values', 'The traditional value requiring a civil servant to serve the elected government of the day neutrally is:', 'Partisanship', 'Political neutrality', 'Populism', 'Activism', 'B', 'Political neutrality requires the permanent civil service to serve any elected government impartially.', 4),
  ('upsc-ethics-public-civil-service-values-q06', 'upsc-ethics-public-civil-service-values', 'Which body in India recommended reforms in its report ''Ethics in Governance''?', 'The First ARC', 'The Law Commission', 'The Second ARC', 'The Finance Commission', 'C', 'The Second Administrative Reforms Commission devoted a report to ''Ethics in Governance''.', 5),
  ('upsc-ethics-public-civil-service-values-q07', 'upsc-ethics-public-civil-service-values', 'Ultimately, in a democracy, a civil servant is accountable to the:', 'Public', 'Media alone', 'Their own family', 'Foreign agencies', 'A', 'A civil servant is accountable to the law, the political executive and ultimately the public.', 6),
  ('upsc-ethics-public-civil-service-values-q08', 'upsc-ethics-public-civil-service-values', 'Which value increasingly emphasised in modern administration relates to compassion for the weak?', 'Aloofness', 'Empathy', 'Indifference', 'Rigidity', 'B', 'Empathy and compassion toward weaker sections are increasingly stressed civil service values.', 7),
  ('upsc-ethics-probity-in-governance-q01', 'upsc-ethics-probity-in-governance', 'Probity in governance essentially means:', 'Integrity and uprightness in public life', 'Speed of decision-making', 'Maximising government revenue', 'Strict secrecy of files', 'A', 'Probity means complete integrity, uprightness and honesty in the conduct of public affairs.', 0),
  ('upsc-ethics-probity-in-governance-q02', 'upsc-ethics-probity-in-governance', 'The Right to Information Act was enacted in which year?', '2002', '2009', '2005', '2013', 'C', 'The Right to Information Act was enacted in 2005 to promote transparency and accountability.', 1),
  ('upsc-ethics-probity-in-governance-q03', 'upsc-ethics-probity-in-governance', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Prevention of Corruption Act was enacted in 1988.
2. The Central Vigilance Commission is the apex integrity watchdog.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'The Prevention of Corruption Act dates to 1988, and the CVC is the apex anti-corruption watchdog.', 2),
  ('upsc-ethics-probity-in-governance-q04', 'upsc-ethics-probity-in-governance', 'A Citizen''s Charter primarily aims to:', 'Declare service standards and grievance redress', 'Increase tax collection', 'Conduct elections', 'Appoint judges', 'A', 'A Citizen''s Charter declares an organisation''s service standards and mechanisms for redress.', 3),
  ('upsc-ethics-probity-in-governance-q05', 'upsc-ethics-probity-in-governance', 'The institution created to act as an ombudsman against corruption at the central level is the:', 'Election Commission', 'NITI Aayog', 'Finance Commission', 'Lokpal', 'D', 'The Lokpal, set up under the Lokpal and Lokayuktas Act, 2013, is the central anti-corruption ombudsman.', 4),
  ('upsc-ethics-probity-in-governance-q06', 'upsc-ethics-probity-in-governance', 'Which Act protects those who expose corruption or wrongdoing?', 'The Official Secrets Act, 1923', 'The Whistle Blowers Protection Act, 2014', 'The Companies Act, 2013', 'The Contempt of Courts Act, 1971', 'B', 'The Whistle Blowers Protection Act, 2014 provides protection to those disclosing corruption.', 5),
  ('upsc-ethics-probity-in-governance-q07', 'upsc-ethics-probity-in-governance', 'Which mechanism, used in MGNREGA, lets the community verify public spending?', 'Social audit', 'Internal audit', 'Statutory audit', 'Forensic audit', 'A', 'Social audit empowers the community to scrutinise public spending, notably under MGNREGA.', 6),
  ('upsc-ethics-probity-in-governance-q08', 'upsc-ethics-probity-in-governance', 'Probity in governance rests primarily on transparency, accountability and the:', 'Discretion of officials', 'Rule of the majority', 'Rule of law', 'Secrecy of decisions', 'C', 'Probity rests on transparency, accountability and the rule of law in public administration.', 7),
  ('upsc-ethics-case-studies-approach-q01', 'upsc-ethics-case-studies-approach', 'An ethical dilemma is best described as a conflict between:', 'A right and a clearly wrong option', 'Law and personal profit', 'Two equally valid right values', 'Two illegal options', 'C', 'An ethical dilemma is a genuine conflict between two competing right values, not right versus wrong.', 0),
  ('upsc-ethics-case-studies-approach-q02', 'upsc-ethics-case-studies-approach', 'In ethics, the principle that good ends do not justify wrong means stresses the importance of:', 'Only the final outcome', 'Means as well as ends', 'Personal gain', 'Speed over correctness', 'B', 'Ethical administration insists that the means must be as legitimate as the ends sought.', 1),
  ('upsc-ethics-case-studies-approach-q03', 'upsc-ethics-case-studies-approach', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Identifying stakeholders is a key step in a case study.
2. The decision should be justified with reasons.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'Both 1 and 2', 'D', 'A sound case-study answer identifies stakeholders and gives a reasoned justification for the chosen action.', 2),
  ('upsc-ethics-case-studies-approach-q04', 'upsc-ethics-case-studies-approach', 'The ''publicity test'' for an ethical decision asks whether you would:', 'Keep it strictly secret', 'Be willing to defend it publicly', 'Maximise personal benefit', 'Obey superiors blindly', 'B', 'The publicity test asks whether you could openly justify and defend the decision before the public.', 3),
  ('upsc-ethics-case-studies-approach-q05', 'upsc-ethics-case-studies-approach', 'Which of the following is typically the FIRST step in analysing a case study?', 'State the facts and identify the dilemma', 'Announce the final decision', 'Punish the wrongdoer', 'Ignore the stakeholders', 'A', 'The first step is to understand the facts clearly and identify the central ethical dilemma.', 4),
  ('upsc-ethics-case-studies-approach-q06', 'upsc-ethics-case-studies-approach', 'A frequent dilemma in case studies is the conflict between:', 'Two unrelated hobbies', 'Personal ethics and professional duty', 'Two foreign policies', 'Weather and climate', 'B', 'Conflicts between personal ethics and professional or official duty are common case-study dilemmas.', 5),
  ('upsc-ethics-case-studies-approach-q07', 'upsc-ethics-case-studies-approach', 'Evaluating each option against ethics and law before deciding is important because it ensures the choice is:', 'Arbitrary', 'Based on personal bias', 'Defensible and reasoned', 'Hidden from scrutiny', 'C', 'Weighing options against ethics and law makes the final decision defensible and well reasoned.', 6),
  ('upsc-ethics-case-studies-approach-q08', 'upsc-ethics-case-studies-approach', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Pressure from political superiors is a recurring case-study theme.
2. The legality and conscience checks help resolve dilemmas.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', '1 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'A', 'Pressure from superiors is common, and legality plus conscience checks guide a reasoned resolution.', 7),
  ('upsc-governance-governance-and-e-governance-q01', 'upsc-governance-governance-and-e-governance', 'The Digital India programme was launched in which year?', '2014', '2015', '2016', '2017', 'B', 'The Digital India programme was launched in 2015 to transform India into a digitally empowered society.', 0),
  ('upsc-governance-governance-and-e-governance-q02', 'upsc-governance-governance-and-e-governance', 'In e-governance, ''G2C'' interaction refers to:', 'Government to Citizen', 'Government to Business', 'Government to Government', 'Government to Employee', 'A', 'G2C denotes Government to Citizen service delivery in the e-governance framework.', 1),
  ('upsc-governance-governance-and-e-governance-q03', 'upsc-governance-governance-and-e-governance', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Accountability and transparency are pillars of good governance.
2. e-Governance can reduce discretion and corruption.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'B', 'Good governance rests on accountability and transparency, and e-governance curbs discretion and graft.', 2),
  ('upsc-governance-governance-and-e-governance-q04', 'upsc-governance-governance-and-e-governance', 'Which platform allows citizens to store official documents digitally?', 'DigiLocker', 'MyGov', 'GeM', 'PRAGATI', 'A', 'DigiLocker provides citizens secure cloud-based storage and access to official documents.', 3),
  ('upsc-governance-governance-and-e-governance-q05', 'upsc-governance-governance-and-e-governance', 'Common Service Centres (CSCs) are mainly intended to:', 'Replace courts', 'Conduct elections', 'Deliver digital services at the last mile', 'Print currency', 'C', 'CSCs deliver government and digital services to citizens at the last mile, especially in rural areas.', 4),
  ('upsc-governance-governance-and-e-governance-q06', 'upsc-governance-governance-and-e-governance', 'The ''JAM trinity'' enabling Direct Benefit Transfer comprises Jan Dhan, Aadhaar and:', 'Microfinance', 'Mobile', 'Markets', 'Mandis', 'B', 'The JAM trinity is Jan Dhan accounts, Aadhaar and Mobile numbers, enabling Direct Benefit Transfer.', 5),
  ('upsc-governance-governance-and-e-governance-q07', 'upsc-governance-governance-and-e-governance', 'The motto ''Minimum Government, Maximum Governance'' emphasises:', 'Expanding bureaucracy', 'Reducing citizen services', 'Centralising all power', 'Simplification and process re-engineering', 'D', 'The motto stresses simplifying processes and reducing red tape while improving service delivery.', 6),
  ('upsc-governance-governance-and-e-governance-q08', 'upsc-governance-governance-and-e-governance', 'The Sevottam model is associated with:', 'Service delivery standards and grievance redress', 'Defence procurement', 'Foreign trade', 'Monetary policy', 'A', 'The Sevottam model sets standards for public service delivery and grievance redress.', 7),
  ('upsc-governance-transparency-rti-and-accountability-q01', 'upsc-governance-transparency-rti-and-accountability', 'The Right to Information flows mainly from which Fundamental Right?', 'Article 21', 'Article 32', 'Article 14', 'Article 19(1)(a) freedom of speech and expression', 'D', 'The RTI is read into Article 19(1)(a), the freedom of speech and expression.', 0),
  ('upsc-governance-transparency-rti-and-accountability-q02', 'upsc-governance-transparency-rti-and-accountability', 'Under the RTI Act, information is normally to be provided within:', '15 days', '45 days', '30 days', '60 days', 'C', 'The RTI Act requires information to be furnished within 30 days of the request in normal cases.', 1),
  ('upsc-governance-transparency-rti-and-accountability-q03', 'upsc-governance-transparency-rti-and-accountability', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The CAG audits government accounts under Article 148.
2. The Public Accounts Committee scrutinises government spending.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'The CAG audits accounts under Article 148, and the PAC examines audited government expenditure.', 2),
  ('upsc-governance-transparency-rti-and-accountability-q04', 'upsc-governance-transparency-rti-and-accountability', 'The apex appellate body under the RTI Act at the central level is the:', 'Central Information Commission', 'Central Vigilance Commission', 'Central Administrative Tribunal', 'National Human Rights Commission', 'A', 'The Central Information Commission is the apex appellate authority under the RTI Act at the Centre.', 3),
  ('upsc-governance-transparency-rti-and-accountability-q05', 'upsc-governance-transparency-rti-and-accountability', 'When information concerns the life or liberty of a person, the RTI reply must be given within:', '15 days', '7 days', '48 hours', '30 days', 'C', 'Where life or liberty is involved, the RTI Act mandates a response within 48 hours.', 4),
  ('upsc-governance-transparency-rti-and-accountability-q06', 'upsc-governance-transparency-rti-and-accountability', 'Which tool lets a local community directly verify the use of public funds?', 'Statutory audit', 'Performance budgeting', 'Social audit', 'Zero-based budgeting', 'C', 'Social audit allows the community to verify how public funds are spent, as in MGNREGA.', 5),
  ('upsc-governance-transparency-rti-and-accountability-q07', 'upsc-governance-transparency-rti-and-accountability', 'The CAG is described as the:', 'Chief electoral officer', 'Head of the executive', 'Guardian of the public purse', 'Custodian of foreign reserves', 'C', 'The Comptroller and Auditor General is called the guardian of the public purse.', 6),
  ('upsc-governance-transparency-rti-and-accountability-q08', 'upsc-governance-transparency-rti-and-accountability', 'RTI exemptions for certain intelligence and security organisations are listed in the:', 'First Schedule', 'Second Schedule', 'Third Schedule', 'Fourth Schedule', 'B', 'The Second Schedule of the RTI Act lists exempt intelligence and security organisations.', 7),
  ('upsc-governance-welfare-schemes-and-vulnerable-sections-q01', 'upsc-governance-welfare-schemes-and-vulnerable-sections', 'Untouchability is abolished by which Article of the Constitution?', 'Article 14', 'Article 15', 'Article 17', 'Article 21', 'C', 'Article 17 abolishes untouchability and forbids its practice in any form.', 0),
  ('upsc-governance-welfare-schemes-and-vulnerable-sections-q02', 'upsc-governance-welfare-schemes-and-vulnerable-sections', 'The National Commission for Scheduled Castes is provided for under which Article?', 'Article 340', 'Article 338A', 'Article 338B', 'Article 338', 'D', 'Article 338 provides for the National Commission for Scheduled Castes.', 1),
  ('upsc-governance-welfare-schemes-and-vulnerable-sections-q03', 'upsc-governance-welfare-schemes-and-vulnerable-sections', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Forest Rights Act was enacted in 2006.
2. It recognises rights of forest-dwelling communities.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', '1 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'A', 'The Forest Rights Act, 2006 recognises the rights of forest-dwelling Scheduled Tribes and other dwellers.', 2),
  ('upsc-governance-welfare-schemes-and-vulnerable-sections-q04', 'upsc-governance-welfare-schemes-and-vulnerable-sections', 'The National Commission for Backward Classes became a constitutional body under which Article?', 'Article 338', 'Article 338B', 'Article 338A', 'Article 340', 'B', 'The 102nd Amendment inserted Article 338B, giving the NCBC constitutional status.', 3),
  ('upsc-governance-welfare-schemes-and-vulnerable-sections-q05', 'upsc-governance-welfare-schemes-and-vulnerable-sections', 'The Rights of Persons with Disabilities Act was enacted in which year?', '1995', '2006', '2013', '2016', 'D', 'The Rights of Persons with Disabilities Act was enacted in 2016, expanding recognised disabilities to 21.', 4),
  ('upsc-governance-welfare-schemes-and-vulnerable-sections-q06', 'upsc-governance-welfare-schemes-and-vulnerable-sections', 'Which scheme targets the welfare of women and children through nutrition support?', 'Make in India', 'Poshan Abhiyaan', 'Stand-Up India', 'Smart Cities Mission', 'B', 'Poshan Abhiyaan aims to improve nutritional outcomes for children, pregnant women and mothers.', 5),
  ('upsc-governance-welfare-schemes-and-vulnerable-sections-q07', 'upsc-governance-welfare-schemes-and-vulnerable-sections', 'Special provisions enabling the State to make laws for women and children are found in:', 'Article 32', 'Article 19(1)(a)', 'Article 25', 'Article 15(3)', 'D', 'Article 15(3) allows the State to make special provisions for women and children.', 6),
  ('upsc-governance-welfare-schemes-and-vulnerable-sections-q08', 'upsc-governance-welfare-schemes-and-vulnerable-sections', 'Administration of tribal areas in states like Assam, Meghalaya and Mizoram is governed by the:', 'Fifth Schedule', 'Sixth Schedule', 'Seventh Schedule', 'Eighth Schedule', 'B', 'The Sixth Schedule governs the administration of tribal areas in Assam, Meghalaya, Tripura and Mizoram.', 7),
  ('upsc-governance-health-education-and-human-resources-q01', 'upsc-governance-health-education-and-human-resources', 'Ayushman Bharat PM-JAY provides health cover of how much per family per year?', '5 lakh', '3 lakh', '1 lakh', '10 lakh', 'A', 'PM-JAY provides health cover of 5 lakh rupees per family per year for secondary and tertiary care.', 0),
  ('upsc-governance-health-education-and-human-resources-q02', 'upsc-governance-health-education-and-human-resources', 'The Right of Children to Free and Compulsory Education Act was enacted in:', '2002', '2005', '2009', '2016', 'C', 'The RTE Act, 2009 operationalises Article 21A, guaranteeing free education to children aged 6 to 14.', 1),
  ('upsc-governance-health-education-and-human-resources-q03', 'upsc-governance-health-education-and-human-resources', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The National Medical Commission replaced the Medical Council of India.
2. The NEP 2020 introduced a 5+3+3+4 school structure.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'The NMC replaced the MCI in 2020, and the NEP 2020 introduced the 5+3+3+4 schooling structure.', 2),
  ('upsc-governance-health-education-and-human-resources-q04', 'upsc-governance-health-education-and-human-resources', 'Which body regulates higher education and universities in India?', 'SEBI', 'The RBI', 'The UGC', 'The NITI Aayog', 'C', 'The University Grants Commission (UGC) regulates standards in higher education and universities.', 3),
  ('upsc-governance-health-education-and-human-resources-q05', 'upsc-governance-health-education-and-human-resources', 'The Human Development Index combines income with which two dimensions?', 'Inflation and employment', 'Savings and consumption', 'Trade and investment', 'Health and education', 'D', 'The HDI combines health (life expectancy), education and per capita income.', 4),
  ('upsc-governance-health-education-and-human-resources-q06', 'upsc-governance-health-education-and-human-resources', 'The NEP 2020 targets a Gross Enrolment Ratio in higher education of about what level by 2035?', '50 per cent', '40 per cent', '30 per cent', '60 per cent', 'A', 'The NEP 2020 aims to raise the higher-education Gross Enrolment Ratio to 50 per cent by 2035.', 5),
  ('upsc-governance-health-education-and-human-resources-q07', 'upsc-governance-health-education-and-human-resources', 'Health and education in India largely fall under which legislative list?', 'Union List', 'Concurrent List', 'State List', 'Residuary powers', 'B', 'Both health-related matters and education are largely on the Concurrent List shared by Centre and States.', 6),
  ('upsc-governance-health-education-and-human-resources-q08', 'upsc-governance-health-education-and-human-resources', 'India''s potential ''demographic dividend'' depends most critically on:', 'Rising death rates', 'Reducing literacy', 'Skilling its young workforce', 'Cutting health spending', 'C', 'The demographic dividend is realised only if the large young population is educated and skilled.', 7),
  ('upsc-internal-security-internal-security-challenges-q01', 'upsc-internal-security-internal-security-challenges', 'Which is India''s principal anti-terror law?', 'The NIA Act, 2008', 'The PMLA, 2002', 'The Arms Act, 1959', 'The UAPA, 1967', 'D', 'The Unlawful Activities (Prevention) Act, 1967 is India''s principal anti-terror legislation.', 0),
  ('upsc-internal-security-internal-security-challenges-q02', 'upsc-internal-security-internal-security-challenges', 'Which agency investigates terror-related offences at the national level?', 'The CBI', 'The Intelligence Bureau', 'The Enforcement Directorate', 'The National Investigation Agency', 'D', 'The National Investigation Agency (NIA) investigates terror offences under the NIA Act, 2008.', 1),
  ('upsc-internal-security-internal-security-challenges-q03', 'upsc-internal-security-internal-security-challenges', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Left-Wing Extremism has been called India''s single biggest internal security threat.
2. The CRPF is the lead force for anti-Naxal operations.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'B', 'LWE was termed the biggest internal security threat, and the CRPF leads anti-Naxal operations.', 2),
  ('upsc-internal-security-internal-security-challenges-q04', 'upsc-internal-security-internal-security-challenges', 'The 2019 amendment to the UAPA notably allowed the government to designate as terrorists:', 'Only organisations', 'Only foreign nationals', 'Only convicted persons', 'Individuals as well', 'D', 'The 2019 UAPA amendment empowered the government to designate individuals, not just organisations, as terrorists.', 3),
  ('upsc-internal-security-internal-security-challenges-q05', 'upsc-internal-security-internal-security-challenges', 'Insurgency in India has been most persistently associated with which region?', 'Kerala', 'The North-East', 'Gujarat', 'Goa', 'B', 'Several North-Eastern states have witnessed long-running insurgencies over identity and autonomy.', 4),
  ('upsc-internal-security-internal-security-challenges-q06', 'upsc-internal-security-internal-security-challenges', 'Which of the following is a Central Armed Police Force?', 'The Indian Navy', 'The Territorial Army', 'The Indian Air Force', 'The CISF', 'D', 'The CISF is one of the Central Armed Police Forces, alongside the CRPF, BSF, ITBP and SSB.', 5),
  ('upsc-internal-security-internal-security-challenges-q07', 'upsc-internal-security-internal-security-challenges', 'The corridor of districts affected by Left-Wing Extremism is popularly called the:', 'Golden Corridor', 'Red Corridor', 'Green Corridor', 'Blue Corridor', 'B', 'The belt of LWE-affected districts in central and eastern India is known as the Red Corridor.', 6),
  ('upsc-internal-security-internal-security-challenges-q08', 'upsc-internal-security-internal-security-challenges', 'Which force is mainly deployed for internal security and law-and-order duties across states?', 'The CRPF', 'The BSF', 'The ITBP', 'The Coast Guard', 'A', 'The Central Reserve Police Force (CRPF) is the lead force for internal security and law and order.', 7),
  ('upsc-internal-security-cyber-security-and-money-laundering-q01', 'upsc-internal-security-cyber-security-and-money-laundering', 'Which is the national nodal agency for responding to cyber security incidents in India?', 'NCIIPC', 'CERT-In', 'NTRO', 'NIA', 'B', 'CERT-In is the national nodal agency for handling cyber security incidents in India.', 0),
  ('upsc-internal-security-cyber-security-and-money-laundering-q02', 'upsc-internal-security-cyber-security-and-money-laundering', 'The primary law dealing with cyber offences in India is the:', 'Indian Penal Code, 1860', 'Telegraph Act, 1885', 'Information Technology Act, 2000', 'Evidence Act, 1872', 'C', 'The Information Technology Act, 2000 is the primary law governing cyber offences in India.', 1),
  ('upsc-internal-security-cyber-security-and-money-laundering-q03', 'upsc-internal-security-cyber-security-and-money-laundering', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Money laundering has three stages: placement, layering and integration.
2. The Enforcement Directorate enforces the PMLA.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', '1 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'A', 'Laundering involves placement, layering and integration, and the ED enforces the PMLA, 2002.', 2),
  ('upsc-internal-security-cyber-security-and-money-laundering-q04', 'upsc-internal-security-cyber-security-and-money-laundering', 'Which global body sets standards against money laundering and terror financing?', 'The IMF', 'The WTO', 'The FATF', 'The OECD', 'C', 'The Financial Action Task Force (FATF) sets global anti-money-laundering and counter-terror-finance standards.', 3),
  ('upsc-internal-security-cyber-security-and-money-laundering-q05', 'upsc-internal-security-cyber-security-and-money-laundering', 'Ransomware is a cyber threat that typically:', 'Speeds up a computer', 'Backs up files automatically', 'Encrypts data and demands payment', 'Improves network security', 'C', 'Ransomware encrypts a victim''s data and demands a ransom for its release.', 4),
  ('upsc-internal-security-cyber-security-and-money-laundering-q06', 'upsc-internal-security-cyber-security-and-money-laundering', 'The agency that receives and analyses suspicious transaction reports in India is the:', 'FIU-IND', 'SEBI', 'CERT-In', 'RBI', 'A', 'The Financial Intelligence Unit-India (FIU-IND) collects and analyses suspicious transaction reports.', 5),
  ('upsc-internal-security-cyber-security-and-money-laundering-q07', 'upsc-internal-security-cyber-security-and-money-laundering', 'An informal value-transfer system often misused for laundering is known as:', 'Hundi insurance', 'Hawala', 'Crowdfunding', 'Factoring', 'B', 'Hawala is an informal, trust-based money-transfer network frequently misused for laundering.', 6),
  ('upsc-internal-security-cyber-security-and-money-laundering-q08', 'upsc-internal-security-cyber-security-and-money-laundering', 'Which body is tasked with protecting India''s critical information infrastructure?', 'NCIIPC', 'CERT-In', 'FIU-IND', 'The Coast Guard', 'A', 'The National Critical Information Infrastructure Protection Centre (NCIIPC) guards critical information assets.', 7),
  ('upsc-internal-security-border-management-q01', 'upsc-internal-security-border-management', 'Which force primarily guards the India-Pakistan and India-Bangladesh borders?', 'The ITBP', 'The Border Security Force', 'The SSB', 'The Assam Rifles', 'B', 'The Border Security Force (BSF) guards the India-Pakistan and India-Bangladesh borders.', 0),
  ('upsc-internal-security-border-management-q02', 'upsc-internal-security-border-management', 'The Indo-Tibetan Border Police primarily guards the border with:', 'Pakistan', 'Bangladesh', 'China', 'Myanmar', 'C', 'The ITBP guards the India-China border along the Line of Actual Control.', 1),
  ('upsc-internal-security-border-management-q03', 'upsc-internal-security-border-management', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Sashastra Seema Bal guards the Nepal and Bhutan borders.
2. The Assam Rifles guards the Myanmar border.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'B', 'The SSB guards the Nepal and Bhutan borders, while the Assam Rifles guards the Myanmar frontier.', 2),
  ('upsc-internal-security-border-management-q04', 'upsc-internal-security-border-management', 'The boundary between India and Pakistan demarcated at Partition is the:', 'McMahon Line', 'Radcliffe Line', 'Durand Line', 'Line of Actual Control', 'B', 'The Radcliffe Line, drawn in 1947, demarcates the India-Pakistan boundary.', 3),
  ('upsc-internal-security-border-management-q05', 'upsc-internal-security-border-management', 'After the 2008 Mumbai attacks, the lead agency for coastal security in territorial waters became the:', 'Indian Navy', 'Indian Coast Guard', 'The BSF', 'The CISF', 'B', 'The Indian Coast Guard was made the lead agency for coastal security in territorial waters after 2008.', 4),
  ('upsc-internal-security-border-management-q06', 'upsc-internal-security-border-management', 'The India-China boundary in the eastern sector is broadly defined by the:', 'Radcliffe Line', 'McMahon Line', 'Durand Line', 'Line of Control', 'B', 'The McMahon Line broadly defines the India-China boundary in the eastern sector.', 5),
  ('upsc-internal-security-border-management-q07', 'upsc-internal-security-border-management', 'The programme that funds development of villages along the border is the:', 'Smart Cities Mission', 'Border Area Development Programme', 'AMRUT', 'PM Gram Sadak Yojana', 'B', 'The Border Area Development Programme (BADP) funds development of border-area villages.', 6),
  ('upsc-internal-security-border-management-q08', 'upsc-internal-security-border-management', 'The technology-based system to seal vulnerable border stretches is the:', 'CIBMS', 'NATGRID', 'CCTNS', 'UMANG', 'A', 'The Comprehensive Integrated Border Management System (CIBMS) uses technology to monitor borders.', 7),
  ('upsc-internal-security-disaster-management-q01', 'upsc-internal-security-disaster-management', 'The Disaster Management Act in India was enacted in which year?', '2000', '2009', '2005', '2013', 'C', 'The Disaster Management Act was enacted in 2005, creating a three-tier institutional structure.', 0),
  ('upsc-internal-security-disaster-management-q02', 'upsc-internal-security-disaster-management', 'The National Disaster Management Authority (NDMA) is chaired by the:', 'Home Minister', 'Cabinet Secretary', 'President', 'Prime Minister', 'D', 'The NDMA is chaired by the Prime Minister of India.', 1),
  ('upsc-internal-security-disaster-management-q03', 'upsc-internal-security-disaster-management', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The State Disaster Management Authority is headed by the Chief Minister.
2. The District Disaster Management Authority is headed by the District Collector.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', '1 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'A', 'The SDMA is headed by the Chief Minister and the DDMA by the District Collector or Magistrate.', 2),
  ('upsc-internal-security-disaster-management-q04', 'upsc-internal-security-disaster-management', 'The global framework guiding disaster risk reduction for 2015-2030 is the:', 'Hyogo Framework', 'Paris Agreement', 'Kyoto Protocol', 'Sendai Framework', 'D', 'The Sendai Framework (2015-2030) guides global disaster risk reduction with four priorities.', 3),
  ('upsc-internal-security-disaster-management-q05', 'upsc-internal-security-disaster-management', 'The specialised force for disaster response in India is the:', 'BSF', 'CRPF', 'NDRF', 'Territorial Army', 'C', 'The National Disaster Response Force (NDRF) is the specialised force for disaster response.', 4),
  ('upsc-internal-security-disaster-management-q06', 'upsc-internal-security-disaster-management', 'The Coalition for Disaster Resilient Infrastructure (CDRI) was launched by India in:', '2015', '2019', '2017', '2021', 'B', 'India launched the Coalition for Disaster Resilient Infrastructure (CDRI) in 2019.', 5),
  ('upsc-internal-security-disaster-management-q07', 'upsc-internal-security-disaster-management', 'The 1984 Bhopal Gas Tragedy is an example of which type of disaster?', 'Natural disaster', 'Biological disaster', 'Man-made (industrial) disaster', 'Astronomical disaster', 'C', 'The Bhopal Gas Tragedy was a man-made industrial chemical disaster.', 6),
  ('upsc-internal-security-disaster-management-q08', 'upsc-internal-security-disaster-management', 'Activities such as prevention, mitigation and preparedness belong to which phase of disaster management?', 'Response phase', 'Pre-disaster phase', 'Recovery phase', 'Rehabilitation phase', 'B', 'Prevention, mitigation and preparedness are activities of the pre-disaster phase.', 7),
  ('jee-physics-kinematics-1d-q01', 'jee-physics-kinematics-1d', 'A body starts from rest and accelerates at 2 m/s². How far does it travel in 5 s?', '20 m', '25 m', '50 m', '10 m', 'B', 's = ut + ½at² = 0 + ½(2)(25) = 25 m.', 0),
  ('jee-physics-kinematics-1d-q02', 'jee-physics-kinematics-1d', 'A stone is dropped from rest. Its velocity after 3 s (g = 10 m/s²) is:', '10 m/s', '30 m/s', '20 m/s', '45 m/s', 'B', 'v = u + gt = 0 + 10 × 3 = 30 m/s.', 1),
  ('jee-physics-kinematics-1d-q03', 'jee-physics-kinematics-1d', 'The area under a velocity–time graph represents:', 'Acceleration', 'Displacement', 'Jerk', 'Average speed', 'B', 'Integrating velocity over time gives displacement, which is the area under the v–t curve.', 2),
  ('jee-physics-kinematics-1d-q04', 'jee-physics-kinematics-1d', 'A car moving at 20 m/s decelerates uniformly and stops in 100 m. The deceleration is:', '2 m/s²', '10 m/s²', '1 m/s²', '4 m/s²', 'A', 'Using v² = u² + 2as: 0 = 400 + 2a(100), so a = −2 m/s².', 3),
  ('jee-physics-kinematics-1d-q05', 'jee-physics-kinematics-1d', 'The distance covered in the n-th second by a body from rest with acceleration a is:', '(a/2)(2n − 1)', 'an', '½an²', 'a(n − 1)', 'A', 's_nth = u + (a/2)(2n − 1); with u = 0 it reduces to (a/2)(2n − 1).', 4),
  ('jee-physics-kinematics-1d-q06', 'jee-physics-kinematics-1d', 'A ball thrown vertically up with 20 m/s reaches a maximum height of (g = 10 m/s²):', '20 m', '10 m', '30 m', '40 m', 'A', 'At the top v = 0, so h = u²/2g = 400/20 = 20 m.', 5),
  ('jee-physics-kinematics-1d-q07', 'jee-physics-kinematics-1d', 'If velocity is negative and acceleration is positive, the body is:', 'Slowing down', 'Speeding up', 'At rest', 'Moving at constant speed', 'A', 'Opposite signs of v and a mean the speed (magnitude) is decreasing.', 6),
  ('jee-physics-kinematics-1d-q08', 'jee-physics-kinematics-1d', 'Two balls are dropped 1 s apart from the same height. As they fall, the gap between them:', 'Stays constant', 'Decreases', 'First increases then decreases', 'Increases', 'D', 'The earlier ball is always faster, so the separation grows with time.', 7),
  ('jee-physics-rotational-motion-q01', 'jee-physics-rotational-motion', 'The moment of inertia of a solid sphere about a diameter is:', 'MR²', '(2/5)MR²', '(1/2)MR²', '(2/3)MR²', 'B', 'A uniform solid sphere has I = (2/5)MR² about any diameter.', 0),
  ('jee-physics-rotational-motion-q02', 'jee-physics-rotational-motion', 'The rotational analogue of force is:', 'Momentum', 'Torque', 'Impulse', 'Power', 'B', 'Torque τ = Iα plays the role of force F = ma in rotation.', 1),
  ('jee-physics-rotational-motion-q03', 'jee-physics-rotational-motion', 'A skater pulls in her arms while spinning. Her angular velocity:', 'Stays the same', 'Decreases', 'Increases', 'Becomes zero', 'C', 'With torque zero, L = Iω is conserved; reducing I increases ω.', 2),
  ('jee-physics-rotational-motion-q04', 'jee-physics-rotational-motion', 'Which body reaches the bottom of an incline first while rolling without slipping?', 'Solid sphere', 'Hollow sphere', 'Ring', 'Hollow cylinder', 'A', 'The solid sphere has the smallest I/MR² (2/5), giving the largest acceleration.', 3),
  ('jee-physics-rotational-motion-q05', 'jee-physics-rotational-motion', 'The parallel axis theorem states I = :', 'I_cm − Md²', 'I_cm + Md²', 'I_cm + ½Md²', '2I_cm + Md²', 'B', 'I about a parallel axis equals the centre-of-mass value plus Md².', 4),
  ('jee-physics-rotational-motion-q06', 'jee-physics-rotational-motion', 'For rolling without slipping, the velocity of the contact point with the ground is:', 'Zero', 'v/2', '2v', 'v', 'A', 'In pure rolling, the instantaneous velocity of the contact point is zero.', 5),
  ('jee-physics-rotational-motion-q07', 'jee-physics-rotational-motion', 'The rotational kinetic energy of a body is:', '½Iω²', 'Iω²', '½Iω', '½I²ω', 'A', 'Rotational KE = ½Iω², analogous to ½mv² for translation.', 6),
  ('jee-physics-rotational-motion-q08', 'jee-physics-rotational-motion', 'A disc of moment of inertia 2 kg·m² spins at 3 rad/s. Its angular momentum is:', '3 kg·m²/s', '9 kg·m²/s', '6 kg·m²/s', '5 kg·m²/s', 'C', 'L = Iω = 2 × 3 = 6 kg·m²/s.', 7),
  ('jee-chemistry-chemical-bonding-q01', 'jee-chemistry-chemical-bonding', 'The shape of a molecule with sp³ hybridisation and no lone pairs is:', 'Trigonal planar', 'Tetrahedral', 'Linear', 'Octahedral', 'B', 'Four equivalent sp³ orbitals point to the corners of a tetrahedron (109.5°).', 0),
  ('jee-chemistry-chemical-bonding-q02', 'jee-chemistry-chemical-bonding', 'The bond angle in a water molecule is approximately:', '90°', '109.5°', '104.5°', '120°', 'C', 'Two lone pairs on the sp³ oxygen compress the H–O–H angle to about 104.5°.', 1),
  ('jee-chemistry-chemical-bonding-q03', 'jee-chemistry-chemical-bonding', 'Which molecule has a zero net dipole moment despite polar bonds?', 'NH₃', 'CO₂', 'HCl', 'H₂O', 'B', 'CO₂ is linear and symmetric, so the two bond dipoles cancel exactly.', 2),
  ('jee-chemistry-chemical-bonding-q04', 'jee-chemistry-chemical-bonding', 'The bond order of the oxygen molecule (O₂) from MO theory is:', '2', '1', '1.5', '3', 'A', 'O₂ has a bond order of 2 and two unpaired electrons, making it paramagnetic.', 3),
  ('jee-chemistry-chemical-bonding-q05', 'jee-chemistry-chemical-bonding', 'According to Fajans'' rules, covalent character increases with:', 'Large cation, small anion', 'Small cation, large anion', 'Low cation charge', 'Large anion, large cation', 'B', 'A small, highly charged cation polarises a large anion, increasing covalent character.', 4),
  ('jee-chemistry-chemical-bonding-q06', 'jee-chemistry-chemical-bonding', 'The hybridisation of carbon in ethyne (C₂H₂) is:', 'sp³d', 'sp²', 'sp³', 'sp', 'D', 'The triple-bonded carbons in ethyne are sp hybridised, giving a linear molecule.', 5),
  ('jee-chemistry-chemical-bonding-q07', 'jee-chemistry-chemical-bonding', 'The unusually high boiling point of water is mainly due to:', 'Ionic bonding', 'Van der Waals forces', 'Hydrogen bonding', 'Metallic bonding', 'C', 'Extensive hydrogen bonding between water molecules requires extra energy to break.', 6),
  ('jee-chemistry-chemical-bonding-q08', 'jee-chemistry-chemical-bonding', 'In the ammonium ion (NH₄⁺), the fourth N–H bond is a:', 'Coordinate bond', 'Metallic bond', 'Hydrogen bond', 'Ionic bond', 'A', 'The lone pair on nitrogen forms a coordinate (dative) bond with the proton.', 7),
  ('jee-mathematics-quadratic-equations-q01', 'jee-mathematics-quadratic-equations', 'For the equation x² − 5x + 6 = 0, the sum of the roots is:', '6', '5', '−5', '−6', 'B', 'Sum of roots = −b/a = −(−5)/1 = 5 (roots are 2 and 3).', 0),
  ('jee-mathematics-quadratic-equations-q02', 'jee-mathematics-quadratic-equations', 'The discriminant of 2x² + 3x + 5 = 0 is:', '31', '−49', '49', '−31', 'D', 'D = b² − 4ac = 9 − 40 = −31, so the roots are complex.', 1),
  ('jee-mathematics-quadratic-equations-q03', 'jee-mathematics-quadratic-equations', 'If the roots of a quadratic are equal, the discriminant is:', 'Negative', 'Zero', 'Irrational', 'Positive', 'B', 'Equal real roots occur exactly when D = b² − 4ac = 0.', 2),
  ('jee-mathematics-quadratic-equations-q04', 'jee-mathematics-quadratic-equations', 'The quadratic equation whose roots are 3 and −2 is:', 'x² − 5x + 6 = 0', 'x² + x − 6 = 0', 'x² − x − 6 = 0', 'x² + 5x + 6 = 0', 'C', 'Sum = 1, product = −6, so x² − (1)x + (−6) = x² − x − 6 = 0.', 3),
  ('jee-mathematics-quadratic-equations-q05', 'jee-mathematics-quadratic-equations', 'For ax² + bx + c > 0 to hold for all real x, we require:', 'a > 0 and D > 0', 'a < 0 and D > 0', 'a > 0 and D < 0', 'a < 0 and D < 0', 'C', 'An upward parabola (a > 0) that never touches the x-axis (D < 0) is always positive.', 4),
  ('jee-mathematics-quadratic-equations-q06', 'jee-mathematics-quadratic-equations', 'If α and β are roots of x² − 6x + 8 = 0, then α² + β² equals:', '16', '20', '36', '52', 'B', 'α² + β² = (α + β)² − 2αβ = 36 − 16 = 20.', 5),
  ('jee-mathematics-quadratic-equations-q07', 'jee-mathematics-quadratic-equations', 'The vertex of the parabola y = x² − 4x + 7 lies at x =:', '−2', '1', '4', '2', 'D', 'The vertex is at x = −b/(2a) = 4/2 = 2.', 6),
  ('jee-mathematics-quadratic-equations-q08', 'jee-mathematics-quadratic-equations', 'The product of the roots of 3x² − 12x + 9 = 0 is:', '3', '4', '1', '9', 'A', 'Product = c/a = 9/3 = 3.', 7),
  ('jee-physics-laws-of-motion-q01', 'jee-physics-laws-of-motion', 'A net force of 12 N acts on a 3 kg block. Its acceleration is:', '4 m/s²', '36 m/s²', '9 m/s²', '2 m/s²', 'A', 'By Newton''s second law a = F/m = 12/3 = 4 m/s².', 0),
  ('jee-physics-laws-of-motion-q02', 'jee-physics-laws-of-motion', 'Newton''s third law force pairs always act on:', 'The same body', 'Two different bodies', 'Massless objects only', 'The Earth only', 'B', 'Action and reaction are equal, opposite, and act on different bodies.', 1),
  ('jee-physics-laws-of-motion-q03', 'jee-physics-laws-of-motion', 'A block on a horizontal surface has mu_s = 0.5 and mass 4 kg (g = 10). Maximum static friction is:', '20 N', '40 N', '2 N', '10 N', 'A', 'f_max = mu_s x N = 0.5 x 4 x 10 = 20 N.', 2),
  ('jee-physics-laws-of-motion-q04', 'jee-physics-laws-of-motion', 'The angle of repose theta for a surface with coefficient of friction mu satisfies:', 'sin(theta) = mu', 'cos(theta) = mu', 'theta = mu', 'tan(theta) = mu', 'D', 'A block just slides when tan(theta) equals the coefficient of static friction.', 3),
  ('jee-physics-laws-of-motion-q05', 'jee-physics-laws-of-motion', 'A person of mass 50 kg stands in a lift accelerating up at 2 m/s² (g = 10). Apparent weight is:', '500 N', '400 N', '600 N', '100 N', 'C', 'Apparent weight = m(g + a) = 50 x 12 = 600 N.', 4),
  ('jee-physics-laws-of-motion-q06', 'jee-physics-laws-of-motion', 'Impulse is equal to the change in:', 'Kinetic energy', 'Momentum', 'Acceleration', 'Power', 'B', 'Impulse J = F x t equals the change in momentum, by the impulse-momentum theorem.', 5),
  ('jee-physics-laws-of-motion-q07', 'jee-physics-laws-of-motion', 'Two blocks of 2 kg and 3 kg connected by a string are pulled by 20 N on a frictionless floor. Acceleration is:', '10 m/s²', '4 m/s²', '6.7 m/s²', '2 m/s²', 'B', 'a = F/(m1 + m2) = 20/5 = 4 m/s².', 6),
  ('jee-physics-laws-of-motion-q08', 'jee-physics-laws-of-motion', 'A body in equilibrium under three forces means the forces:', 'Form a closed triangle', 'Are perpendicular', 'Are all equal', 'Have zero magnitude', 'A', 'Three concurrent forces in equilibrium add vectorially to zero, forming a closed triangle.', 7),
  ('jee-physics-work-energy-power-q01', 'jee-physics-work-energy-power', 'A force of 10 N moves a body 5 m in its own direction. Work done is:', '2 J', '15 J', '0 J', '50 J', 'D', 'W = F x s x cos(0) = 10 x 5 = 50 J.', 0),
  ('jee-physics-work-energy-power-q02', 'jee-physics-work-energy-power', 'The kinetic energy of a 2 kg body moving at 3 m/s is:', '9 J', '6 J', '18 J', '3 J', 'A', 'KE = 0.5 x m x v² = 0.5 x 2 x 9 = 9 J.', 1),
  ('jee-physics-work-energy-power-q03', 'jee-physics-work-energy-power', 'Work done by a force perpendicular to the displacement is:', 'Zero', 'Equal to F x s', 'Maximum', 'Negative', 'A', 'W = Fs cos(90) = 0; a perpendicular force does no work.', 2),
  ('jee-physics-work-energy-power-q04', 'jee-physics-work-energy-power', 'A spring of constant 200 N/m is stretched 0.1 m. Potential energy stored is:', '1 J', '2 J', '20 J', '10 J', 'A', 'PE = 0.5 x k x x² = 0.5 x 200 x 0.01 = 1 J.', 3),
  ('jee-physics-work-energy-power-q05', 'jee-physics-work-energy-power', 'In a perfectly inelastic collision, the conserved quantity is:', 'Kinetic energy', 'Momentum', 'Both KE and momentum', 'Neither', 'B', 'Momentum is conserved in all collisions; kinetic energy is lost when inelastic.', 4),
  ('jee-physics-work-energy-power-q06', 'jee-physics-work-energy-power', 'A 1000 W motor lifting a load does how much work in 10 s?', '10000 J', '1000 J', '100000 J', '100 J', 'A', 'W = P x t = 1000 x 10 = 10000 J.', 5),
  ('jee-physics-work-energy-power-q07', 'jee-physics-work-energy-power', 'For a perfectly elastic collision, the coefficient of restitution e equals:', '0', '0.5', '1', '2', 'C', 'e = 1 for elastic collisions; e = 0 for perfectly inelastic ones.', 6),
  ('jee-physics-work-energy-power-q08', 'jee-physics-work-energy-power', 'The instantaneous power delivered by a force F to a body moving at velocity v is:', 'F/v', 'F + v', 'F x v', '0.5 F v²', 'C', 'Instantaneous power P equals the dot product F x v.', 7),
  ('jee-physics-gravitation-q01', 'jee-physics-gravitation', 'The escape velocity from Earth is approximately:', '3.0 km/s', '7.9 km/s', '11.2 km/s', '30 km/s', 'C', 'Earth''s escape velocity is about 11.2 km/s, equal to sqrt(2GM/R).', 0),
  ('jee-physics-gravitation-q02', 'jee-physics-gravitation', 'If the distance between two masses is doubled, the gravitational force becomes:', 'One-quarter', 'Four times', 'Double', 'Half', 'A', 'Force varies as 1/r²; doubling r reduces it to one-quarter.', 1),
  ('jee-physics-gravitation-q03', 'jee-physics-gravitation', 'The value of g at a height equal to Earth''s radius R above the surface is:', 'g/4', 'g/2', 'g', 'g/9', 'A', 'At height R, distance from centre is 2R, so g'' = g/(2)² = g/4.', 2),
  ('jee-physics-gravitation-q04', 'jee-physics-gravitation', 'Kepler''s third law states that the square of the orbital period is proportional to:', 'Cube of the radius', 'Square of the radius', 'Orbital radius', 'Mass of the planet', 'A', 'T² is proportional to r³, Kepler''s law of periods.', 3),
  ('jee-physics-gravitation-q05', 'jee-physics-gravitation', 'The orbital velocity of a satellite close to Earth''s surface relates to escape velocity by:', 'v_e = sqrt(2) v_o', 'v_e = 2 v_o', 'v_e = v_o', 'v_e = v_o/2', 'A', 'Escape velocity is sqrt(2) times the orbital velocity.', 4),
  ('jee-physics-gravitation-q06', 'jee-physics-gravitation', 'The period of a geostationary satellite is:', '365 days', '12 hours', '1 hour', '24 hours', 'D', 'A geostationary satellite matches Earth''s rotation with a 24-hour period.', 5),
  ('jee-physics-gravitation-q07', 'jee-physics-gravitation', 'The gravitational potential energy of two masses separated by r is:', '+GMm/r', '-GMm/r', '-GMm/r²', 'GMm/r²', 'B', 'Gravitational PE is negative: U = -GMm/r, taken zero at infinity.', 6),
  ('jee-physics-gravitation-q08', 'jee-physics-gravitation', 'At the centre of the Earth, the acceleration due to gravity is:', 'Zero', 'Equal to surface g', 'Infinite', 'Maximum', 'A', 'g decreases linearly with depth and is zero at the centre.', 7),
  ('jee-physics-shm-waves-q01', 'jee-physics-shm-waves', 'The time period of a simple pendulum of length L is:', '2*pi*sqrt(L/g)', '2*pi*sqrt(g/L)', '2*pi*sqrt(m/k)', 'sqrt(L/g)', 'A', 'The pendulum period is 2*pi*sqrt(L/g), independent of mass.', 0),
  ('jee-physics-shm-waves-q02', 'jee-physics-shm-waves', 'In SHM, the acceleration is maximum at:', 'The mean position', 'Halfway', 'The extreme position', 'Everywhere equal', 'C', 'Acceleration a = -omega²x is maximum where displacement x is largest, at the extremes.', 1),
