  ('jee-chemistry-amines-q03', 'jee-chemistry-amines', 'The carbylamine test is specific to which type of amine?', 'Quaternary', 'Secondary', 'Tertiary', 'Primary', 'D', 'Only primary amines give the foul-smelling isocyanide in the carbylamine test.', 2),
  ('jee-chemistry-amines-q04', 'jee-chemistry-amines', 'Diazotisation of a primary aromatic amine is carried out at a temperature of:', '60 degrees C', '25 degrees C', '0 to 5 degrees C', '100 degrees C', 'C', 'Diazonium salts are unstable, so diazotisation is done at 0 to 5 degrees C.', 3),
