  ('jee-chemistry-environmental-chemistry-q05', 'jee-chemistry-environmental-chemistry', 'Which gas is the main contributor to the greenhouse effect from fossil fuels?', 'Argon', 'Oxygen', 'Carbon dioxide', 'Hydrogen', 'C', 'Carbon dioxide from burning fossil fuels is the leading greenhouse gas.', 4),
